%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20quartet%20have%20collectively%20poured%20%241.1%20trillion%20into%20buybacks%20since%20early%202013%2C%20more%20than%20the%20market%20value%20of%20Tesla%20(%24805%20billion)%2C%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%20(%24781%20billion)%2C%20or%20Meta%20(%24767%20billion).%20Their%2010-year%20outlay%20also%20rivals%20Nvidia's%20current%20market%20capitalization%20of%20%241.2%20trillion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20companies%20aren't%20far%20behind%20in%20the%20rankings.%20Wells%20Fargo%2C%20Bank%20of%20America%2C%20and%20JPMorgan%20each%20spent%20between%20%24110%20billion%20and%20%24120%20billion%20in%20the%2010-year%20period.%20Home%20Depot%2C%20Berkshire%2C%20and%20Johnson%20%26amp%3B%20Johnson%20rounded%20out%20the%20top%2010%20with%20outlays%20of%20%2470%20billion%2C%20%2477%20billion%2C%20and%20%24113%20billion%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2020%20biggest%20spenders%20have%20spent%20about%20%242%20trillion%20on%20buybacks%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20%E2%80%94%20a%20big%20chunk%20of%20the%20%246.6%20trillion%20deployed%20by%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20companies%20as%20a%20whole%20in%20the%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuybacks%20reduce%20a%20company's%20total%20number%20of%20outstanding%20shares%2C%20increasing%20shareholders'%20ownership.%20Executives%20also%20use%20them%20to%20signal%20they%20believe%20their%20stock%20is%20undervalued%20and%20a%20good%20investment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20they've%20been%20more%20common%20among%20mature%20companies%20that%20are%20focused%20on%20returning%20cash%20to%20shareholders%20instead%20of%20growing%20their%20businesses.%20Technology%20companies%20tend%20to%20have%20better%20uses%20for%20their%20cash%20such%20as%20expansion%2C%20investing%20in%20new%20facilities%20and%20equipment%2C%20researching%20and%20developing%20new%20products%2C%20or%20making%20acquisitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%20Buffett%20is%20famously%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-st