-people-cost-living-most-expensive-us-states-ranked-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693390284000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef086b96b7920019ca397d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhawaii-single-people-cost-living-most-expensive-us-states-ranked-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Single%20people%20need%20an%20annual%20paycheck%20of%20%24112%2C000%20to%20make%20a%20living%20wage%20in%20Hawaii%2C%20an%20analysis%20by%20GoBankingRates%20found.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bnolan%40insider.com%20(Beatrice%20Nolan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhawaii-single-people-cost-living-most-expensive-us-states-ranked-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Turkish%20Family%20Walking%20On%20All%20Fours%20Baffles%20Scientists%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20family%20living%20in%20Turkey%20has%20baffled%20scientists%20studying%20the%20evolution%20of%20humans.%20Certain%20members%20of%20the%20Ulas%20family%20walk%20on%20all%20fours%2C%20which%20had%20not%20been%20observed%20in%20fully-grown%20adults%20before%20this%20discovery.%20This%20unusual%20behaviour%20was%20first%20documented%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F2%2Fhi%2Fscience%2Fnature%2F4782492.stm%5C%22%3E2006%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%20documentary%3C%2Fa%3E%20titled%20'The%20Family%20That%20Walks%20on%20All%20Fours'.%20The%20video%20shows%20the%20members%20of%20the%20family%20using%20the%20palms%20of%20their%20hands%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bbear%20crawl%26quot%3B.%20A%20scientific%20paper%20has%20also%20been%20published%2C%20giving%20details%20about%20the%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20Professor%20Humphrey%2C%20from%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20(LSE)%2C%20as%20saying%20that%20four%20sisters%20and%20one%20brothers%20were%20born%20with%20the%20unusual%20trait%20that%20could%20yield%20clues%20to%20why%20our%20ancestors%20made%20the%20transition%20from%20four-legged%20to%20two-legged%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20a%20sixth%20member%20of%20the%20family%2C%20who%20also%20had%20the%20characteristic%2C%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20never%20expected%20that%20even%20under%20the%20most%20extraordinary%20scientific%20fantasy%20that%20modern%20human%20beings%20could%20return%20to%20an%20animal%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20Professor%20Humphrey%20said%20on%2060%20Minutes%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20which%20marks%20us%20off%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20animal%20world%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20we're%20the%20species%20which%20walks%20on%20two%20legs%20and%20holds%20our%20heads%20high%20in%20the%20air%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20it's%20language%20and%20all%20other%20sorts%20of%20things%20too%2C%20but%20it's%20terribly%20important%20to%20our%20sense%20of%20ourselves%20as%20being%20different%20from%20others%20in%20the%20animal%20kingdom.%20These%20people%20cross%20that%20boundary%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20the%20expert.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20study%20by%20researchers%20at%20Liverpool%20University%20said%20that%20the%20children%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20study%20had%20skeletons%20with%20more%20resemblance%20to%20apes%20than%20humans%20and%20a%20shrunken%20cerebellum%2C%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2023%2F08%2F29%2Ffamily-that-walks-on-all-fours-baffles-scientists-shouldnt-exist%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Humphrey%20later%20said%20that%20a%20physiotherapist%20later%20and%20equipment%20used%20to%20help%20them%20walk%20on%20just%20two%20feet%2C%20which%20led%20to%20significant%20improvements%20in%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693390200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F75jm