sues%20relating%20to%20First%20Nations%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Voice%20to%20Parliament%20has%20been%20toted%20as%20a%20vital%20step%20toward%20redressing%20Australia%E2%80%99s%20painful%20history%20of%20discrimination%20against%20Aboriginal%20and%20Torres%20Strait%20Islander%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20for%20Indigenous%20Australians%2C%20Linda%20Burney%2C%20has%20said%20it%20would%20also%20remedy%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Faustralia-news%2F2023%2Faug%2F28%2Fwhat-is-the-indigenous-voice-to-parliament-australia-what-does-it-mean-explained-referendum-campaign%5C%22%3Elong%20legacy%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20failed%20policies%20on%20a%20variety%20of%20issues%2C%20from%20the%20over-representation%20of%20First%20Nations%20people%20in%20the%20prison%20system%20to%20poorer%20outcomes%20for%20First%20Nations%20people%20in%20health%2C%20employment%20and%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Voice%20represents%20a%20new%20approach.%20Initially%20proposed%20in%20a%20document%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fulurustatement.org%2Fthe-statement%2Fview-the-statement%2F%5C%22%3EUluru%20Statement%20from%20the%20Heart%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20a%20First%20Nations%20constitutional%20convention%20in%202017%2C%20the%20Voice%20would%20be%20enshrined%20in%20the%20Constitution%20to%20ensure%20it%20would%20have%20a%20permanent%20presence%20and%20role%20in%20Australian%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%20a%20referendum%20is%20needed%20%E2%80%93%20and%20why%20this%20particular%20one%20has%20been%20so%20fiercely%20debated%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDecades%20of%20efforts%20toward%20equality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20for%20a%20constitutional%20referendum%20to%20be%20successful%2C%20it%20must%20garner%20a%20majority%20of%20votes%20nationally%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20majority%20of%20votes%20in%20a%20majority%20of%20states%20(this%20means%20four%20of%20the%20six%20states).%20Votes%20in%20Australia%E2%80%99s%20two%20territories%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Australian%20Capital%20Territory%20and%20the%20Northern%20Territory%20%E2%80%93%20will%20count%20toward%20the%20national%20vote%20count%20but%20not%20toward%20the%20majority%20of%20states%20requirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferendums%20don%E2%80%99t%20pass%20frequently.%20Only%20eight%20out%20of%2044%20previous%20referendums%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sbs.com.au%2Fnews%2Farticle%2Fonly-eight-of-australias-44-referendums-were-a-yes%2F7c7o5nfsg%5C%22%3Ehave%20passed%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20time%20Australia%20voted%20on%20a%20referendum%20dealing%20with%20Indigenous%20affairs%20was%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faiatsis.gov.au%2Fexplore%2F1967-referendum%5C%22%3E1967%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fletting-the-people-decide-should-australia-hold-more-referendums-178145%5C%22%3Ereferendum%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20two%20things%20possible%3A%20the%20Commonwealth%20could%20count%20Aboriginal%20and%20Torres%20Strait%20Islander%20people%20in%20the%20national%20census%20and%20make%20laws%20with%20respect%20to%20Aboriginal%20and%20Torres%20Strait%20Islander%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20referendum%20passed%20by%20a%20huge%20margin.%20With%20the%20government%20able%20to%20make%20laws%20about%20First%20Nations%20people%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20it%20ensured%20they%20would%20be%20protected%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.legislation.gov.au%2FDetails%2FC2016C00089%5C%22%3ERacial%20Discrimination%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20was%20passed%20in%201975.%20This%20act%20prohibits%20discrimination%20in%20employment%2C%20housing%20and%20access%20to%20public%20facilities%2C%20such%20as%20swimming%20pools%2C%20cinemas%20and%20shops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20all%20the%201967%20referendum%20made%20possible%2C%20progress%20has%20been%20slow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAboriginal%20and%20Torres%20Strait%20Islanders%20make%20up%20a%20very%20small%20minority%20of%20the%20overall%20Australian%20population%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abs.gov.au%2Fstatistics%2Fpeople%2Faboriginal-and-torres-strait-islander-peoples%2Festimates-aboriginal-and-torres-strait-islander-australians%2Flatest-release%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DMedia%2520releases-%2CKey%2520statistics%2Cof%2520the%2520total%2520Australian%2520population.%5C%22%3Eless%20than%204%25%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20so%20the%20right%20to%20vote%20has%20not%20always%20ensured%20political%20representation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20there%20are%20currently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aph.gov.au%2FAbout_Parliament%2FParliamentary_departments%2FParliamentary_Library%2Fpubs%2Frp%2Frp2223%2FQuick_Guides%2FIndigenousMPs2022%5C%22%3E11%20Aboriginal%20members%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20parliament%2C%20they%20cannot%20represent%20all%20Aboriginal%20people.%20And%20there%20have%20yet%20to%20be%20any%20representatives%20at%20the%20Commonwealth%20level%20from%20the%20Torres%20Strait%20Islands%20(an%20archipelago%20between%20Australia%20and%20Papua%20New%20Guinea).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%E2%80%9Cyes%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cno%E2%80%9D%20campaigns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20lead-up%20to%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20referendum%2C%20the%20nation%20has%20been%20split%20along%20a%20stark%20%E2%80%9Cyes%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cno%E2%80%9D%20divide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%9Cyes%E2%80%9D%20campaign%20has%20declared%20it%E2%80%99s%20time%20for%20change%2C%20emphasising%20how%20governments%20have%20consistently%20failed%20First%20Nations%20communities%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20say%20better%20policy%20decisions%20result%20from%20local%20communities%20being%20heard%20on%20matters%20that%20affect%20them.%20To%20secure%20support%20from%20a%20mostly%20non-Indigenous%20population%2C%20the%20campaign%20also%20presents%20the%20Voice%20as%20an%20opportunity%20for%20all%20Australians%20to%20come%20together%20in%20support%20of%20recognition%20and%20democratic%20renewal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArguments%20against%20the%20Voice%20have%20been%20made%20on%20two%20different%20grounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndependent%20Senator%20Lidia%20Thorpe%2C%20a%20DjabWurrung%2C%20Gunnai%20and%20Gunditjmara%20woman%2C%20has%20argued%20the%20Voice%20is%20a%20powerless%20advisory%20body.%20She%20has%20called%20for%20the%20government%20to%20pursue%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwhat-actually-is-a-treaty-what-could-it-mean-for-indigenous-people-200261%5C%22%3Etreaty%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Aboriginal%20and%20Torres%20Strait%20Islander%20people%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20treaty%20processes%20can%20take%20many%20years%20to%20progress.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20state%20of%20Victoria%20began%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.firstpeoplesrelations.vic.gov.au%2Ftreaty-process%5C%22%3Ea%20treaty%20process%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20First%20Nations%20people%20in%202018%20and%20negotiations%20are%20only%20just%20about%20to%20commence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20%E2%80%9Cno%E2%80%9D%20campaign%2C%20led%20by%20the%20conservative%20opposition%20parties%2C%20has%20depicted%20the%20proposed%20Voice%20as%20a%20body%20for%20elites%20in%20Canberra%2C%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20capital%2C%20which%20would%20be%20divisive%20for%20the%20country%20and%20prone%20to%20judicial%20overreach.%20%E2%80%9CYes%E2%80%9D%20campaigners%20contend%20many%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cno%E2%80%9D%20arguments%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2F10-questions-about-the-voice-to-parliament-answered-by-the-experts-207014%5C%22%3Emisinformation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20significance%20of%20the%20vote%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20after%201967%2C%20it%20remains%20clear%20that%20existing%20voting%20rights%20and%20political%20institutions%20alone%20cannot%20represent%20the%20interests%20of%20Aboriginal%20and%20Torres%20Strait%20Islander%20people%20to%20the%20federal%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternationally%2C%20other%20countries%20have%20attempted%20to%20create%20improved%20political%20participation%20and%20government%20accountability%20for%20Indigenous%20peoples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20New%20Zealand%2C%20for%20example%2C%20there%20is%20designated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwhat-australia-could-learn-from-new-zealand-about-indigenous-representation-201761%5C%22%3EM%C4%81ori%20representation%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20parliament.%20In%20Scandinavia%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsametinget.no%2Fabout-the-sami-parliament%2F%5C%22%3ES%C3%A1mi%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E%20represents%20seven%20Indigenous%20nations%20across%20Finland%2C%20Norway%20and%20Sweden.%20In%20Canada%2C%20First%20Nations%20people%20have%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rcaanc-cirnac.gc.ca%2Feng%2F1307460755710%2F1536862806124%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cfirst-contact%E2%80%9D%20treaties%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atns.net.au%2Ftreaty-canada%5C%22%3Enegotiated%3C%2Fa%3E%20upon%20European%20arrival%2C%20as%20well%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.atns.net.au%2Ftreaty-canada%5C%22%3Emodern%20treaties%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202023%20referendum%20is%20the%20first%20occasion%20Australia%20has%20considered%20how%20Aboriginal%20and%20Torres%20Strait%20Islander%20people%20can%20be%20meaningfully%20represented%20in%20the%20federal%20government.%20Whatever%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20referendum%2C%20it%20will%20send%20a%20powerful%20message%20to%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20about%20how%20Australians%20view%20their%20country.%20%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F212259%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20he