20group%20chats.%3Cp%3EArantza%20Pena%20Popo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGroup%20chats%20and%20messaging%20apps%20killed%20it%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETati%20Bruening%2C%20a%2022-year-old%20content%20creator%20and%20photographer%2C%20just%20wants%20to%20share%20memes%20and%20post%20about%20cooking%20green%20beans.%20Every%20time%20she%20logs%20onto%20Instagram%2C%20however%2C%20her%20feed%20is%20swamped%20by%20a%20combination%20of%20perfectly%20curated%20photos%20and%20professionally%20created%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20bizarre%20to%20me%20that%20everyone's%20gone%20to%20this%20place%20in%20their%20mind%20that%20content%20has%20to%20be%20so%20curated%2C%26quot%3B%20Bruening%20told%20us.%20%26quot%3BSo%20curated%20that%20you%20can't%20show%20what%20you're%20cooking%20for%20dinner%2C%20because%20that's%20not%20cool%20enough.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrustrated%20with%20the%20state%20of%20the%20platform%2C%20Breuning%20launched%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fmake-instagram-instagram-again-the-apps-evolution-is-causing-users-to-question-its-future-11658921581%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMake%20Instagram%20Instagram%20Again''%3C%2Fa%3E%20crusade%20in%202022.%20Using%20her%20handle%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fillumitati%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIllumitati%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20campaign%20pushed%20back%20against%20the%20platform's%20changes%20that%20prioritized%20algorithmically%20suggested%20videos%20over%20a%20chronological%20feed%20of%20accounts%20you%20follow.%20Thousands%20of%20users%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vulture.com%2F2022%2F07%2Finstagram-kylie-jenner-criticizes-algorithm-reels.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeven%20some%20celebrities%20like%20Kylie%20Jenner%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20got%20on%20board.%20Soon%20enough%2C%20Instagram%20scaled%20back%20its%20aggressive%20recommendations%20push.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20core%20of%20Bruening's%20frustration%20was%20a%20sea%20change%20that%20had%20swept%20across%20Instagram%3A%20Instead%20of%20everyday%20photos%20from%20regular%20people%2C%20the%20platform%20had%20become%20a%20curated%20platform%20where%20even%20seemingly%20authentic%20content%20was%20meticulously%20planned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fatigue%20average%20people%20feel%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20posting%20on%20Instagram%20has%20pushed%20more%20users%20toward%20private%20posting%20and%20closed%20groups.%20Features%20like%20Close%20Friends%20(a%20private%20list%20of%20people%20who%20have%20access%20to%20your%20content)%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20group%20chats%20give%20people%20a%20safer%20place%20to%20share%20memes%2C%20gossip%20with%20friends%2C%20and%20even%20meet%20new%20people.%20It's%20less%20pressure%20%E2%80%94%20%3Cem%3Ethey%20won't%20mind%20if%20I%20didn't%20blur%20out%20the%20pimple%20on%20my%20forehead%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20but%20this%20side%20of%20Instagram%20hardly%20fulfills%20the%20original%20free-flowing%C2%A0%20promise%20of%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20this%20very%20weird%2C%20unspoken%20social%20standard%20of%20what's%20allowed%20on%20Instagram%2C%26quot%3B%20Bruening%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20that%20for%20my%20age%20group%2C%20it's%20like%20you%20give%20up%20on%20it%20entirely%2C%20and%20then%20you%20just%20post%20only%20to%20your%20Close%20Friends%20or%20alternate%20accounts.%20There's%20this%20sublayer%20of%20Instagram%20that's%20much%20more%20true%20to%20what%20the%20app%20once%20was%2C%20but%20it%20is%20just%20not%20viewable%20to%20the%20general%20public.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBruening%20isn't%20alone.%20Despite%20the%20efforts%20of%20big%20incumbents%20and%20buzzy%20new%20apps%2C%20the%20old%20ways%20of%20posting%20are%20gone%2C%20and%20people%20don't%20want%20to%20go%20back.%20Even%20Adam%20Mosseri%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Instagram%2C%20admitted%20that%20users%20have%20moved%20on%20to%20direct%20messages%2C%20closed%20communities%2C%20and%20group%20chats.%20Regularly%20posting%20content%20is%20now%20largely%20confined%20to%20content%20creators%20and%20influencers%2C%20while%20non-creators%20are%20moving%20toward%20sharing%20bits%20of%20their%20lives%20behind%20private%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20people%20have%20been%20confronted%20with%20the%20consequences%20of%20constant%20sharing%2C%20social%20media%20has%20become%20less%20social%20and%20more%20media%20%E2%80%94%20a%20constellation%20of%20entertainment%20platforms%20where%20users%20consume%20content%20but%20rarely%2C%20if%20ever%2C%20create%20their%20own.%20Influencers%2C%20marketers%2C%20average%20users%2C%20and%20even%20social-media%20executives%20agree%3A%20Social%20media%2C%20as%20we%20once%20knew%20it%2C%20is%20dead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ESocial%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20media%20to%20social%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Emedia%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20app%20better%20defines%20the%20changing%20nature%20of%20social%20media%20than%20Instagram.%20The%20app%20started%20as%20a%20digital%20scrapbook%20%E2%80%94%20a%20place%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20real-world%20connections%2C%20close%20friends%2C%20and%20family.%20While%20other%20networks%20had%20more%20users%20(Facebook)%20or%20generated%20more%20news%20(Twitter)%2C%20Instagram%20seemed%20to%20define%20the%20ideal%20form%20of%20this%20era%20of%20social%20media.%20Instagram%20became%20a%20verb%2C%20an%20aesthetic%2C%20and%20a%20generational%20signifier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20sort%20of%20end%20up%20in%20this%20world%20that%20is%20beautiful%20and%20you%20are%20following%20your%20friends%20and%20following%20your%20family%2C%26quot%3B%20Jeffrey%20Gerson%2C%20a%20former%20Instagram%20product-marketing%20manager%2C%20told%20us%20about%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20app.%20%26quot%3BHow%20often%20do%20you%20get%20the%20chance%20to%20see%20the%20world%20through%20your%20second%20cousin's%20eyes%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20Instagram%20grew%20up%2C%20things%20began%20to%20change.%20Sarah%20Frier%2C%20a%20Bloomberg%20tech%20reporter%20and%20editor%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BNo%20Filter%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20chronicles%20the%20history%20of%20Instagram%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2020%2F10%2F7%2F21506016%2Finstagram-10-year-anniversary-sarah-frier-interview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20that%20users%20learned%20curation%20from%20the%20introduction%20of%20photo%20filters%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20filters%20and%20editing%20tools%20came%20hashtags%2C%20an%20explore%20tab%2C%20and%20the%20option%20to%20privately%20save%20people's%20photos.%20What%20was%20once%20an%20enjoyable%20pastime%20became%20a%20minefield%20of%20considerations%3A%20What%20should%20I%20say%20in%20the%20caption%3F%20Are%20emojis%20still%20cool%3F%20Is%20it%20better%20to%20just%20stay%20mysterious%20and%20let%20the%20images%20speak%20for%20themselves%3F%20This%20running%20list%20of%20questions%20made%20the%20posting%20process%20overwhelming%2C%20robbing%20Instagram%20of%20its%20early%20magic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThere's%20this%20very%20weird%2C%20unspoken%20social%20standard%20of%20what's%20allowed%20on%20Instagram.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20posting%20became%20higher%20stakes%2C%20new%20features%20also%20pushed%20users%20away%20from%20the%20original%20mission%3A%20Instagram%20began%20prioritizing%20video%2C%20then%20livestreaming%2C%20and%20then%20shopping.%20Each%20change%20muddled%20the%20purpose%20of%20Instagram%20even%20further.%20Everyday%20people%20were%20still%20posting%20to%20the%20platform%2C%20but%20more%20and%20more%20of%20the%20content%20became%20professionalized.%20Bloggers%20brought%20their%20audience%2C%20editing%20skills%2C%20and%20expensive%20cameras%20to%20the%20platform.%20Influencers%20started%20to%20snag%20brand%20deals%2C%20and%20fashion%20bloggers%20made%20the%20platform%20into%20a%20career.%20Instagram%20encouraged%20the%20rise%20of%20influencers%20with%20programs%20that%20helped%20creators%20understand%20best%20practices%2C%20gave%20them%20technical%20support%2C%20and%20set%20up%20discreet%20payment%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20app%20has%20become%20an%20aspirational%20entertainment%20app%20%E2%80%94%20a%20place%20where%20users%20can%20shop%2C%20find%20information%2C%20and%20get%20inspired%20(or%2C%20more%20commonly%2C%20overwhelmed)%20by%20snapshots%20of%20the%20best%20moments%20of%20a%20person's%20life.%20Nearly%20every%20photo%20on%20Instagram%20now%20is%20hand%20selected%20from%20an%20album%20of%20dozens%20of%20nearly%20identical%20images.%20The%20only%20difference%20is%20the%20one%20you're%20seeing%20isn't%20too%20perfect%20but%20just%20perfect%20enough%20for%20sharing.%20These%20shifts%20had%20a%20downstream%20effect%20on%20everyday%20users%3A%20The%20cadence%20of%20posting%20content%20changed.%20%26quot%3BYour%20friends%20don't%20post%20that%20much%20to%20feed%2C%26quot%3B%20Mosseri%20admitted%20during%20a%20recent%20interview%20on%20the%20%26quot%3B20VC%26quot%3B%20podcast.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHannah%20Stowe%2C%20a%2023-year-old%20who%20lives%20in%20New%20York%2C%20said%20that%20while%20she%20uses%20Instagram%20every%20day%2C%20she%20rarely%20finds%20herself%20posting%20these%20days.%20%26quot%3BI%20used%20to%20post%20on%20Instagram%20weekly%2Fbimonthly%2C%20but%20now%20it's%20much%20less%20frequent%2C%20like%20four%20or%20five%20times%20a%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20us%20in%20a%20DM.%20%26quot%3BI%20add%20stories%20more%20impulsively%20but%20way%20less%20than%20I%20used%20to.%20Now%20it's%20probably%20like%20once%20a%20week.%20If%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20sharing%20has%20tailed%20off%2C%20consuming%20content%20hasn't%20slowed%2C%20especially%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Andrea%20Casanova%2C%20an%20influencer%20strategist%2C%20told%20us.%20When%20people%20were%20confined%20to%20their%20homes%2C%20the%20apps%20saw%20an%20influx%20of%20photos%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20people%20who%20either%20have%20a%20specific%20lifestyle%20or%20had%20specific%20talents%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20This%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20reinforces%20typical%20people's%20decision%20to%20not%20post%20on%20their%20own%20feeds%2C%20Casanova%20said%2C%20because%20they%20assume%20the%20bar%20for%20what%20people%20want%20to%20see%20is%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCulture%20in%20general%20has%20kept%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20from%20showing%20up%20because%20they%20don't%20think%20their%20life%20is%20aesthetic%2C%20or%20they%20don't%20think%20that%20they're%20selling%20anything%2C%20so%20why%20would%20they%20post%20on%20social%20media%3F%20'I%20just%20don't%20have%20the%20lifestyle%20that%20all%20of%20these%20creators%20have%2C%20so%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20I%20would%20be%20sharing'%20and%20therefore%20fall%20into%20this%20loop%20of%20never%20sharing%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20Casanova%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20users%20post%20less%20and%20less%20to%20Instagram%2C%20new%20apps%20have%20tried%20to%20stake%20their%20claim%20as%20the%20next%20big%20thing.%20The%20French%20social-media%20app%20BeReal%2C%20which%20gained%20popularity%20for%20its%20more%20authentic%20experience%2C%20peaked%20at%2075%20million%20downloads%20per%20analytics%20firm%20Sensor%20Tower%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbereal-buzzy-gen-z-social-media-app-raise-630m-valuation-2022-5%5C%22%3E%24630%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20valuation.%20Growth%20has%20stalled%20a%20year%20later%2C%20with%20a%20monthly%20active%20user%20base%20of%2051%20million%2C%20a%20sliver%20of%20Instagram's%201.4%20billion.%20Other%20apps%20like%20Dispo%2C%20Poparazzi%2C%20and%20Locket%20have%20all%20used%20various%20gimmicks%20to%20try%20and%20recapture%20social%20media's%20halcyon%20days%20%E2%80%94%20each%20had%20a%20moment%20in%20the%20sun%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20US%20Apple%20app-store%20charts%20%E2%80%94%20but%20none%20have%20truly%20broken%20through.%20Even%20ByteDance%2C%20which%20has%20the%20same%20parent%20company%20as%20TikTok%2C%20failed%20to%20recapture%20the%20fading%20magic%20with%20the%20photo-sharing%20platform%20Lemon8.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EI'm%20honestly%20just%20tired%20of%20social%20media.%20I'm%20tired%20of%20consuming%20content%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%20there%20is%20Threads%2C%20Instagram's%20latest%20play%20in%20the%20space%20to%20fill%20the%20void%20that%20was%20left%20as%20Twitter%20has%20undergone%20so%20much%20volatility.%20While%20Mosseri%20has%20hailed%20the%20text-focused%20platform%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bless%20angry%20place%20for%20conversations%2C%20%26quot%3B%20Threads'%20daily%20active-user%20count%20is%20down%2079%25%20a%20month%20after%20it%20launched%20%E2%80%94%20to%2010.3%20million%20daily%20active%20users%2C%20data%20from%20Similarweb%20found.%20Even%20with%20the%20backing%20of%20Meta%2C%20Threads%20may%20not%20have%20the%20juice%20to%20make%20it%20through%2C%20because%20it%20doesn't%20offer%20users%20a%20new%20way%20to%20interact.%20It%20follows%20in%20the%20footsteps%20of%20other%20buzzy%20startups%20that%20rise%20to%20the%20top%20for%20weeks%2C%20even%20days%2C%20before%20users%20get%20bored.%20The%20core%20issue%20is%20that%20these%20apps%20don't%20solve%20anything%20new.%20They%20are%20mostly%20copycat%20versions%20of%20each%20other.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20looking%20for%20that%20'groundbreaking%20app%2C'%20and%20we%20still%20haven't%20gotten%20that%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20Casanova%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20going%20down%20in%20the%20DMs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20era%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20frequent%20social-media%20users%20are%20sick%20of%20being%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2Fpkbpk7%2Fits-normal-to-feel-anxious-about-being-seen-and-perceived-after-covid-pandemic-v28n2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperceived%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20having%20hundreds%2C%20or%20even%20thousands%2C%20of%20eyes%20on%20them%2C%20many%20are%20retreating%20to%20the%20days%20of%20tighter%20connections%20and%20communities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20honestly%20just%20tired%20of%20social%20media%2C%26quot%3B%20said%2023-year-old%20Walid%20Malb%2C%20who%20works%20in%20the%20creator%20economy.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20tired%20of%20consuming%20content%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20Instagram%20was%20the%20bellwether%20for%20the%20rise%20and%20fall%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bsocial%26quot%3B%20social-media%20era%2C%20it%20is%20also%20a%20harbinger%20of%20this%20new%20era.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20how%20teens%20spend%20their%20time%20on%20Instagram%2C%20they%20spend%20more%20time%20in%20DMs%20than%20they%20do%20in%20stories%2C%20and%20they%20spend%20more%20time%20in%20stories%20than%20they%20do%20in%20feed%2C%26quot%3B%20Mosseri%20said%20during%20the%20%26quot%3B20VC%26quot%3B%20interview.%20Given%20this%20changing%20behavior%2C%20Mosseri%20said%20the%20platform%20has%20shifted%20its%20resources%20to%20messaging%20tools.%20%26quot%3BActually%2C%20at%20one%20point%20a%20couple%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20think%20I%20put%20the%20entire%20stories%20team%20on%20messaging%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20closed%20spaces%20aren't%20just%20more%20private%20than%20the%20Instagrams%20and%20TikToks%20of%20social%20media%2C%20however%20%E2%80%94%20they%20also%20offer%20something%20algorithms%20can't%20serve%3A%20niche%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20this%20really%20interesting%20countermovement%20backwards%20into%20these%20much%20smaller%20and%20much%20more%20hyper-specific%20communities%2C%26quot%3B%20s