20behemoths%20like%20Instagram%20are%20also%20trying%20to%20capitalize%20on%20this%20reality%20by%20introducing%20features%20like%20paid-subscription%20services%20that%20offer%20exclusive%20group%20chats.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EYou%20have%20this%20really%20interesting%20countermovement%20backwards%20into%20these%20much%20smaller%20and%20much%20more%20hyper-specific%20communities.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcreator-economy-influencer-marketing-experts-to-follow-linkedin-newsletters-podcasts-2023-5%23lia-haberman-is-a-college-professor-who-writes-a-weekly-newsletter-breaking-down-the-latest-influencer-marketing-news-11%5C%22%3ELia%20Haberman%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20adjunct%20professor%20at%20UCLA%20Extension%20and%20an%20advisor%20for%20the%20American%20Influencer%20Council%2C%20said%20that%20Gen%20Alpha%2C%20the%20age%20cohort%20of%2013%20and%20younger%2C%20are%20%26quot%3Bnot%20embracing%20traditional%20social-media%20platforms%20and%20customs.%26quot%3B%20This%20presents%20a%20problem%20for%20influencers%20and%20brands%2C%20since%20smaller%2C%20more%20direct%20spaces%20are%20harder%20to%20penetrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20does%20a%20brand%20show%20up%20in%20somebody's%20DMs%20or%20Discord%20server%20if%20they're%20not%20invited%3F%26quot%3B%20Haberman%20said.%20But%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20that's%20the%20point.%20People%20can%20still%20go%20on%20Instagram%20to%20check%20on%20their%20favorite%20celebrities%20and%20influencers%2C%20but%20young%20people%20don't%20want%20brands%20and%20marketers%20infiltrating%20the%20closed%20communities%20where%20they%20spend%20most%20of%20their%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20promised%20to%20create%20an%20intricate%20web%20that%20brought%20us%20all%20closer%20to%20one%20another%2C%20but%20the%20wave%20of%20exposure%20led%20to%20an%20openness%20that%20many%20people%20just%20aren't%20interested%20in.%20Most%20people%20wouldn't%20let%20the%20first%20person%20they%20stop%20on%20the%20street%20sift%20through%20their%20camera%20roll.%20They%20want%20their%20achievements%2C%20failures%2C%20and%20little%20life%20moments%20to%20be%20kept%20sacred.%20So%20after%20a%20decade%20of%20airing%20our%20most%20intimate%20moments%20in%20public%2C%20the%20pendulum%20is%20shifting%20back.%20People%20are%20more%20selective%20with%20their%20communities%20and%20are%20reverting%20back%20to%20an%20old-school%20way%20of%20interacting.%20It's%20hard%20to%20know%20how%20the%20change%20will%20affect%20the%20online%20atmosphere%20over%20the%20long%20term%20%E2%80%94%20some%20evidence%20suggests%20the%20shift%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-media-twitter-facebook-political-polarization-mechanism-2022-10%5C%22%3Ecreate%20a%20healthier%20digital%20experience%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it%20also%20risks%20further%20dividing%20people%20into%20like-minded%20echo%20chambers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhatever%20the%20result%2C%20it's%20clear%20that%20the%20Instagram%20era%20of%20social%20media%20is%20over%20and%20the%20new%20era%20of%20%26quot%3Bauthentic%26quot%3B%20online%20sharing%20is%20emerging%20%E2%80%94%20just%20without%20an%20audience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-perelli%5C%22%3EAmanda%20Perelli%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20creator%20economy%20reporter%20covering%20social%20media%20influencers%2C%20advertising%20and%20marketing%20trends%20for%20Insider.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fsydney-bradley%5C%22%3ESydney%20Bradley%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20covering%20the%20creator%20economy%2C%20influencers%2C%20and%20tech%20for%20Insider.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-media-dead-instagram-tiktok-bereal-replaced-group-chats-messaging-2023-8%5C%2