mers%20will%20visit%20and%20either%20see%20an%20ad%2C%20subscribe%2C%20or%20buy%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20though%2C%20generative%20AI%20and%20large%20language%20models%20are%20changing%20the%20mission%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gptbot-web-crawler-content-creators-ai-bots-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweb%20crawlers%3C%2Fa%3E%20radically%20and%20rapidly.%20Instead%20of%20working%20to%20support%20content%20creators%2C%20these%20tools%20have%20been%20turned%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20bots%20feeding%20Big%20Tech%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWeb%20crawlers%20now%20collect%20online%20information%20to%20feed%20into%20giant%20datasets%20that%20are%20used%20for%20free%20by%20wealthy%20tech%20companies%20to%20develop%20AI%20models.%20CCBot%20feeds%20Common%20Crawl%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20AI%20datasets.%20GPTbot%20feeds%20data%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-cant-identify-ai-generated-text-bad-for-internet-models-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20behind%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gpt4-ai-model-got-lazier-dumber-chatgpt-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGPT-4%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20currently%20the%20most%20powerful%20AI%20model.%20Google%20just%20calls%20its%20LLM%20training%20data%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2201.08239.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInfiniset%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20without%20mentioning%20where%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20data%20comes%20from.%20Although%2012.5%25%20comes%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhuggingface.co%2Fdatasets%2Fc4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EC4%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20cleaned%20up%20version%20of%20Common%20Crawl.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20models%20use%20all%20this%20free%20information%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20answer%20user%20questions%20immediately.%20That's%20a%20long%20way%20from%20indexing%20a%20web%20site%20so%20users%20can%20be%20sent%20through%20to%20the%20original%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20a%20supply%20of%20potential%20consumers%2C%20there's%20little%20incentive%20for%20content%20creators%20to%20let%20web%20crawlers%20continue%20to%20suck%20up%20free%20data%20online.%20GPTbot%20is%20already%20being%20blocked%20by%20Amazon%2C%20Airbnb%2C%20Quora%2C%20and%20hundreds%20of%20other%20websites.%20Common%20Crawl's%20CCBot%20is%20beginning%20to%20be%20blocked%20more%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'A%20crude%20tool'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20hasn't%20changed%20is%20%3Cem%3Ehow%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20block%20these%20crawlers.%20Implementing%20robots.txt%20on%20a%20web%20site%2C%20and%20excluding%20specific%20crawlers%2C%20is%20the%20only%20option.%20And%20it's%20not%20very%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20crude%20tool%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Joost%20de%20Valk%2C%20a%20former%20Wordpress%20executive%2C%20tech%20investor%20and%20founder%20of%20digital%20marketing%20firm%20Yoast.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20no%20basis%20in%20law%2C%20and%20is%20basically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdevelopers.google.com%2Fsearch%2Fblog%2F2019%2F07%2Frep-id%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emaintained%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Google%2C%20although%20they%20say%20they%20do%20that%20together%20with%20other%20search%20engines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20open%20to%20manipulation%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20voracious%20appetite%20for%20quality%20AI%20data.%20The%20only%20thing%20a%20company%20like%20OpenAI%20has%20to%20change%20is%20the%20name%20of%20its%20bot%20crawler%20to%20bypass%20all%20the%20disallow%20rules%20people%20put%20in%20place%20using%20robots.txt%2C%20de%20Valk%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20robots.txt%20is%20voluntary%2C%20web%20crawlers%20can%20also%20simply%20ignore%20the%20blocking%20instructions%20and%20siphon%20the%20information%20from%20a%20site%20anyway.%20Some%20crawlers%2C%20like%20that%20of%20Brave%2C%20a%20newer%20search%20engine%2C%20don't%20bother%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstackdiary.com%2Fbrave-selling-copyrighted-data-for-ai-training%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edisclosing%20the%20name%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20their%20crawler%2C%20making%20it%20impossible%20to%20block.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20online%20is%20being%20sucked%20up%20into%20a%20vacuum%20for%20the%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nick%20Vincent%2C%20a%20computer%20science%20professor%20who%20studies%20the%20relationship%20between%20human-generated%20data%20and%20AI.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20so%20much%20going%20on%20under%20the%20hood.%20In%20the%20next%20six%20months%2C%20we%20will%20look%20back%20and%20want%20to%20evaluate%20these%20models%20differently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAI%20bot%20backlash%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDe%20Valk%20warns%20that%20owners%20and%20creators%20of%20online%20content%20may%20already%20be%20too%20late%20in%20understanding%20the%20risks%20of%20allowing%20these%20bots%20to%20scoop%20up%20their%20data%20for%20free%20and%20use%20it%20indiscriminately%20to%20develop%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20doing%20nothing%20means%2C%20'I'm%20ok%20with%20my%20content%20being%20in%20every%20AI%20and%20LLM%20in%20the%20world%2C'%20de%20Valk%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20just%20plain%20wrong.%20A%20better%20version%20of%20robots.txt%20could%20be%20created%2C%20but%20it'd%20be%20very%20weird%20if%20that%20was%20done%20by%20the%20search%20engines%20and%20the%20large%20AI%20parties%20themselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20major%20companies%20and%20websites%20have%20responded%20recently%2C%20with%20some%20starting%20to%20deploy%20robots.txt%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20August%2022%2C%2070%20of%20the%201%2C000%20most-popular%20websites%20have%20used%20robots.txt%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-openai-gptbot-crawler-major-companies-media-outlets-blocking-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eblock%20GPTBot%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20OpenAI%20revealed%20the%20crawler%20about%20three%20weeks%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FOriginality.ai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOriginality.ai%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20company%20that%20checks%20content%20to%20see%20if%20it's%20AI-generated%20or%20plagiarized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20found%20that%2062%20of%20the%201%2C000%20most%20popular%20websites%20are%20blocking%20Common%20Crawl's%20CCBot%2C%20with%20an%20increasing%20number%20doing%20so%20only%20this%20year%20as%20awareness%20of%20data%20crawling%20for%20AI%20has%20grown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it%20is%20not%20enforceable.%20Any%20crawler%20could%20ignore%20a%20robots.txt%20file%20and%20collect%20every%20last%20bit%20of%20data%20it%20found%20on%20a%20webpage%2C%20with%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20page%20more%20than%20likely%20having%20no%20idea%20it%20even%20happened.%20Even%20if%20robots.txt%20had%20any%20basis%20in%20law%2C%20its%20original%20purpose%20has%20little%20to%20do%20with%20information%20on%20the%20internet%20being%20used%20to%20create%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRobots.txt%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20legal%20prohibition%20on%20use%20of%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Jason%20Schultz%2C%20director%20of%20NYU's%20Technology%20Law%20%26amp%3B%20Policy%20Clinic.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20primarily%20meant%20to%20signal%20that%20one%20did%20not%20want%20one's%20website%20to%20be%20indexed%20by%20search%20engines%2C%20not%20as%20a%20signal%20that%20one%20did%20not%20want%20one's%20content%20used%20for%20machine%20learning%20and%20AI%20training.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'This%20is%20a%20minefield'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20activity%20has%20been%20going%20on%20for%20years.%20OpenAI%20revealed%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.openai.com%2Fresearch-covers%2Flanguage-unsupervised%2Flanguage_understanding_paper.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efirst%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20GPT%20model%20in%202018%2C%20having%20trained%20it%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fdirty-secrets-of-bookcorpus-a-key-dataset-in-machine-learning-6ee2927e8650%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EBookCorpus%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20dataset%20of%20thousands%20of%20indie%20or%20self-published%20books.%20Common%20Crawl%20started%20in%202008%20and%20its%20dataset%20became%20publicly%20available%20in%202011%20through%20cloud%20storage%20provided%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fregistry.opendata.aws%2Fcommoncrawl%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAWS%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20GPTBot%20is%20now%20more%20widely%20blocked%2C%20Common%20Crawl%20is%20a%20larger%20threat%20to%20any%20business%20that%20is%20concerned%20about%20its%20data%20being%20used%20to%20train%20another%20company's%20AI%20model.%20What%20Google%20did%20for%20internet%20search%2C%20Common%20Crawl%20is%20doing%20for%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20minefield%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Catherine%20Stihler%2C%20CEO%20of%20Creative%20Commons.%20%26quot%3BWe%20updated%20our%20strategy%20only%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20now%20we're%20in%20a%20different%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreative%20Commons%20started%20in%202001%20as%20a%20way%20for%20creators%20and%20owners%20to%20license%20works%20for%20use%20on%20the%20internet%20through%20an%20alternative%20to%20strict%20a%20copyright%20framework%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bcopyleft.%26quot%3B%20Creators%20and%20owners%20maintain%20their%20rights%2C%20while%20a%20Commons%20license%20let%20people%20access%20the%20content%20and%20create%20derivative%20works.%20Wikipedia%20operates%20through%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license%2C%20as%20does%20Flickr%2C%20Stack%20Overflow%20and%20ProPublica%2C%20along%20with%20many%20other%20well-known%20websites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20it's%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F10rQDv5Hzuss38oi1ovGuoxHagmFzqn_f%2Fview%3Fpli%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efive%20year%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20notes%20the%20%26quot%3Bproblematic%20use%20of%20open%20content%26quot%3B%20to%20train%20AI%20technologies%2C%20Creative%20Commons%20is%20looking%20to%20make%20the%20sharing%20of%20work%20online%20more%20%26quot%3Bequitable%2C%26quot%3B%20through%20a%20%26quot%3Bmultifrontal%2C%20coordinated%2C%20broad-based%20approach%20that%20transcends%20copyright.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20160%20billion-page%20gorilla%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECommon%20Crawl%2C%20via%20CCBot%2C%20holds%20what%20is%20perhaps%20the%20largest%20repository%20of%20data%20ever%20collected%20from%20the%20internet.%20Since%202011%2C%20it%20has%20crawled%20and%20saved%20information%20from%20160%20billion%20web%20pages%20and%20counting.%20Typically%20it%20crawls%20and%20saves%20around%203%20billion%20web%20pages%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20mission%20statement%20says%20the%20undertaking%20is%20an%20%26quot%3Bopen%20data%26quot%3B%20project%20aimed%20at%20allowing%20anyone%20to%20%26quot%3Bindulge%20their%20curiosities%2C%20analyze%20the%20world%2C%20and%20pursue%20brilliant%20ideas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20has%20become%20very%20different%20today.%20The%20massive%20amount%20of%20data%20it%20holds%20and%20continues%20to%20collect%20is%20being%20used%20by%20some%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20corporations%20to%20create%20mostly%20proprietary%20models.%20If%20a%20big%20tech%20company%20isn't%20already%20making%20money%20off%20of%20its%20AI%20output%20(OpenAI%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fpricing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20paid%20services%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20there's%20a%20plan%20to%20do%20so%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20big%20tech%20companies%20have%20stopped%20disclosing%20where%20they%20get%20this%20data.%20However%2C%20Common%20Crawl%20has%20been%20and%20continues%20to%20be%20used%20to%20develop%20many%20powerful%20AI%20models.%20It%20helped%20Google%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2201.08239.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreate%20Bard.%3C%2Fa%3E%20It%20helped%20Meta%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscontent-sjc3-1.xx.fbcdn.net%2Fv%2Ft39.8562-6%2F333078981_693988129081760_4712707815225756708_n.pdf%3F_nc_cat%3D108%26ccb%3D1-7%26_nc_sid%3Dad8a9d%26_nc_ohc%3DvdrPv_dtawYAX_Jc-pk%26_nc_ht%3Dscontent-sjc3-1.xx%26oh%3D00_AfBrNSnHVOiA60fHbLVhoQWTNUjvzL5dZWnJBjTnScpXGA%26oe%3D64F30C62%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrain%20Llama%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20helped%20OpenAI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.openai.com%2Fbetter-language-models%2Flanguage_models_are_unsupervised_multitask_learners.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuild%20ChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommon%20Crawl%20also%20feeds%20The%20Pile%2C%20which%20hosts%20more%20curated%20datasets%20pulled%20from%20the%20work%20of%20other%20bot%20crawlers.%20It%20has%20been%20used%20extensively%20on%20AI%20projects%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2205.01068.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20Llama%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20an%20LLM%20from%20Microsoft%20and%20Nvidia%2C%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fventurebeat.com%2Fai%2Fmicrosoft-and-nvidia-team-up-to-train-one-of-the-worlds-largest-language-models%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMT-NLG%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENot%20comical%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20The%20Pile's%20most%20recent%20downloads%20from%20June%20is%20a%20massive%20collection%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthe-eye.eu%2Fpublic%2FComics%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecomic%20books%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20the%20entire%20works%20of%20Archie%2C%20Batman%2C%20X-Men%2C%20Star%20Wars%20and%20Superman.%20Created%20by%20DC%20Comics%2C%20now%20owned%20by%20Warner%20Brothers%2C%20and%20Marvel%2C%20now%20owned%20by%20Disney%2C%20all%20of%20the%20works%20remain%20under%20copyright.%20The%20Pile%20also%20hosts%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Ftechnology%2Farchive%2F2023%2F08%2Fbooks3-ai-meta-llama-pirated-books%2F675063%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elarge%20set%20of%20copyrighted%20books%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20The%20Atlantic%20recently%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20difference%20between%20the%20intent%20of%20crawlers%20and%20how%20they%20are%20used%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20NYU's%20Schultz.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20very%20hard%20to%20police%20or%20insist%20that%20data%20be%20used%20in%20a%20particular%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20The%20Pile%20is%20concerned%2C%20while%20it%20admits%20its%20data%20is%20full%20of%20copyrighted%20material%2C%20it%20claimed%20in%20its%20founding%20technical%20paper%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20little%20acknowledgment%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20processing%20and%20distribution%20of%20data%20owned%20by%20others%20may%20also%20be%20a%20violation%20of%20copyright%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20that%2C%20the%20group%2C%20part%20of%20EleutherAI%2C%20argued%20its%20use%20of%20the%20material%20is%20considered%20%26quot%3Btransformative%26quot%3B%20under%20the%20fair%20use%20doctrine%2C%20despite%20the%20data%20sets%20holding%20relatively%20unaltered%20work.%20It%20also%20admitted%20that%20it%20needs%20to%20use%20full-length%20copyrighted%20content%20%26quot%3Bin%20order%20to%20produce%20the%20best%20results%26quot%3B%20when%20training%20LLMs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20arguments%20of%20fair%20use%20by%20crawlers%20and%20AI%20projects%20are%20already%20being%20put%20to%20the%20test.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Flegal%2Flawsuit-says-openai-violated-us-authors-copyrights-train-ai-chatbot-2023-06-29%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAuthors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Flegal%2Fai-companies-ask-us-court-dismiss-artists-copyright-lawsuit-2023-04-19%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evisual%20artists%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Flegal%2Flitigation%2Fopenai-microsoft-want-court-toss-lawsuit-accusing-them-abusing-open-source-code-2023-01-27%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esource%20code%20developers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20suing%20the%20likes%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20Microsoft%20and%20Meta%20because%20their%20original%20work%20has%20been%20used%20without%20their%20consent%20to%20train%20something%20they%20get%20no%20benefit%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20universe%20where%20putting%20something%20on%20the%20internet%20grants%20free%2C%20unlimited%2C%20commercial%20use%20of%20someone's%20labor%20w%2Fo%20consent%2C%26quot%3B%20Steven%20Sinofsky%2C%20a%20former%20Microsoft%20executive%20who's%20a%20partner%20at%20VC%20firm%20Andreessen%20Horowitz%2C%20wrote%20recently%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENo%20resolution%20in%20sight%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20moment%2C%20there's%20no%20clear%20resolution%20in%20sight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20grappling%20with%20all%20of%20this%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stihler%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Creative%20Commons.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20so%20many%20issues%20that%20keep%20cropping%20up%3A%20compensation%2C%20consent%2C%20credit.%20What%20does%20all%20of%20that%20look%20like%20with%20AI%3F%20I%20don't%20have%20an%20answer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDe%20Valk%20said%20Creative%20Commons%2C%20with%20its%20method%20of%20facilitating%20broader%20copyright%20licenses%20that%20allow%20owned%20works%20to%20be%20used%20on%20the%20internet%2C%20has%20been%20suggested%20as%20a%20possible%20model%20for%20consent%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20AI%20model%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStihler%20is%20not%20so%20sure.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20AI%2C%20perhaps%20there%20is%20no%20single%20solution.%20Licensing%20and%20copyright%2C%20even%20a%20more%20flexible%20Commons-style%20agreement%2C%20likely%20won't%20work.%20How%20do%20you%20license%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20internet%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20lawyer%20that%20I%20speak%20to%20says%20a%20license%20is%20not%20going%20to%20solve%20the%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Stihler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20is%20talking%20about%20this%20regularly%20to%20stakeholders%2C%20from%20authors%20to%20executives%20of%20AI%20companies.%20Stihler%20with%20representatives%20of%20OpenAI%20earlier%20this%20year%20and%20said%20the%20company%20is%20discussing%20how%20to%20%26quot%3Breward%20creators.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it's%20unclear%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20the%20commons%20really%20looks%20like%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'If%20we're%20not%20careful%2C%20we'll%20end%20up%20closing%20the%20commons'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EConsidering%20just%20how%20much%20data%20web%20crawlers%20have%20already%20scraped%20and%20handed%20over%20to%20big%20tech%20companies%2C%20and%20how%20little%20power%20is%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20creators%20of%20that%20content%2C%20the%20internet%20as%20we%20know%20it%20could%20change%20dramatically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20posting%20information%20online%20means%20giving%20data%20for%20free%20to%20an%20AI%20model%20that%20will%20compete%20with%20you%20for%20users%2C%20then%20this%20activity%20may%20simply%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20already%20signs%20of%20this%3A%20Fewer%20human%20software%20coders%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstack-overflow-crisis-future-of-online-data-ai-world-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evisiting%20Q%26amp%3BA%20web%20site%20Stack%20Overflow%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20answer%20questions.%20Why%3F%20Because%20their%20pr