mentary%20historian%20and%20aspiring%20Liberal%20politician%20A.F.%20Pollard%20repeated%20the%20claim%20that%20parliaments%20were%20%E2%80%98incomparably%20the%20greatest%20gift%20of%20the%20English%20people%20to%20the%20civilization%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2F-%2Fes%2FKeane%2Fdp%2F6071655692%5C%22%3E%20%3Ci%3ELa%20Vida%20y%20Muerte%20de%20la%20Democracia%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20%3C%2Fi%3E(2018)%20politely%20questioned%20this%20English%20prejudice.%20It%20showed%20how%2C%20in%20the%20spring%20month%20of%20March%201188%2C%20in%20the%20walled%2C%20former%20Roman%20town%20of%20L%C3%A9on%2C%20a%20full%20generation%20before%20King%20John%E2%80%99s%20Magna%20Carta%20of%201215%2C%20Alfonso%20IX%20did%20something%20extraordinary%3A%20he%20invented%20an%20instrument%20of%20government%20soon%20to%20be%20called%20a%20cortes%2C%20or%20parliament.%20A%20politically%20autonomous%20space%20where%20differences%20of%20opinion%20were%20freely%20debated%20and%20laws%20made%20peacefully%20based%20on%20negotiated%20agreements%20among%20representatives%20of%20various%20social%20interests%20drawn%20from%20a%20wide%20geographic%20radius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20remarkable%20invention%20came%20laced%20with%20ironies.%20The%20cortes%20was%20among%20Europe%E2%80%99s%20first%20precious%20gifts%20to%20the%20world%20of%20modern%20representative%20democracy%2C%20yet%20the%20unfashionable%20word%20%E2%80%98democracy%E2%80%99%20played%20no%20role%20in%20its%20birth.%20The%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20parliament%20stood%20for%20the%20open%20acceptance%20of%20differences%2C%20yet%20it%20was%20a%20child%20of%20recolonisation%20and%20empire%20building.%20Its%20birth%20was%20a%20moment%20in%20the%20Reconquista%2C%20a%20bitter%20military%20struggle%20of%20Christians%20to%20snatch%20fields%20and%20towns%20from%20the%20Muslims%20of%20northern%20Iberia%2C%20to%20set%20Spain%20on%20a%20course%20to%20become%20the%20greatest%20political%20power%20in%20early%20modern%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20epicentre%20of%20these%20ironies%20stood%20King%20Alfonso%20IX%20of%20Le%C3%B3n%20(1188%20-1230).%20At%20the%20ripe%20age%20of%20seventeen%2C%20returning%20from%20exile%20in%20Portugal%2C%20he%20accepted%20the%20crown%20of%20a%20kingdom%20beset%20with%20military%2C%20monetary%20and%20morale%20troubles.%20The%20young%20king%20was%20inexperienced%2C%20wet%20behind%20the%20ears%2C%20but%20he%20caught%20his%20doubters%20and%20foes%20off%20guard.%20He%20sprang%20a%20big%20surprise.%20Was%20he%20the%20bullfighter%20so%20sure%20of%20his%20coming%20demise%20that%20fear%20lost%20its%20grip%20and%20courage%20enabled%20his%20fightback%3F%20Did%20exile%20teach%20him%20the%20art%20of%20historical%20timing%2C%20the%20precious%20sixth%20sense%20of%20knowing%20what%20will%20work%20and%20what%20won%E2%80%99t%20work%20in%20any%20given%20circumstance%3F%20Had%20he%20been%20inspired%20by%20the%20royal%20meeting%20(%3Cem%3Ecuria%3C%2Fem%3E)%20convened%20in%20neighbouring%20Castile%20the%20year%20before%2C%20when%20town%20representatives%20(%3Cem%3Emaiores%3C%2Fem%3E)%20were%20among%20the%20dignitaries%20who%20assembled%20to%20confirm%20the%20right%20of%20accession%20to%20the%20throne%20of%20Queen%20Berenguela%2C%20whom%20he%20later%20married%3F%20We%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20sure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30122559%2Fleon.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30122559%2Fleon.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30122559%2Fleon-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30122559%2Fleon-1024x512.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30122559%2Fleon-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670610%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKing%20Alfonso%20IX%20of%20Le%C3%B3n.%20Photo%3A%20Alonso%20de%20Cartagena1%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20clear%20is%20that%20Alfonso%20chose%20to%20fight%20his%20way%20out%20of%20a%20tight%20corner%20by%20convening%20a%20first-ever%20meeting%20with%20representatives%20of%20the%20leading%20local%20estates.%20Gambling%20with%20his%20crown%2C%20making%20compromises%20that%20might%20have%20destroyed%20his%20kingly%20powers%2C%20young%20Alfonso%20IX%20turned%20to%20the%20local%20nobility%2C%20the%20warrior%20aristocrats%20who%20were%20committed%20in%20their%20bones%20to%20the%20reconquest%20of%20their%20lands.%20He%20called%20as%20well%20on%20the%20bishops%20of%20the%20church%2C%20the%20estate%20that%20saw%20itself%20as%20the%20guardian%20of%20souls%2C%20and%20the%20spiritual%20protector%20of%20God%E2%80%99s%20lands%3B%20and%20he%20summoned%20the%20citizens%20of%20the%20towns%20(%3Ci%3Ecives%3C%2Fi%3E)%2C%20moneyed%20%E2%80%98good%20men%E2%80%99%20(%3Ci%3Eboni%20homines%3C%2Fi%3E)%20respected%20for%20their%20role%20as%20elected%20officers%20of%20the%20town%20councils%20called%20fueros.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20from%20inside%20this%20medieval%20triangle%20comprising%20the%20nobles%2C%20bishops%20and%20urban%20citizens%20%E2%80%93%20the%20representatives%20of%20soldiers%2C%20souls%20and%20money%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20modern%20practice%20of%20parliamentary%20representation%20was%20born.%20It%20was%20one%20of%20those%20magical%20moments%20when%20the%20participants%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20possibly%20have%20known%20the%20world-historical%20significance%20of%20what%20they%20were%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20happened%20in%20L%C3%A9on%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20breaking%20news.%20This%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20yet%20the%20age%20of%20breaking%20news%2C%20but%20the%20first-ever%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20as%20contemporaries%20soon%20christened%20it%2C%20radically%20altered%20the%20poetry%20of%20politics.%20It%20gave%20a%20new%20meaning%20to%20the%20word%20itself%2C%20which%20until%20then%20had%20been%20the%20local%20term%20for%20both%20the%20town%20where%20a%20king%20resides%20and%20a%20city%20council%20whose%20representatives%20made%20proposals%20and%20demands%20and%20granted%20services%20to%20a%20monarch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20word%20representation%20(%3Ci%3Eprocurador%3C%2Fi%3E)%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20an%20outside%20chance%20that%20locals%20had%20absorbed%20the%20notion%20from%20local%20Muslims%2C%20for%20whom%20a%20legal%20representative%20(%3Ci%3Ew%C4%81kil%3C%2Fi%3E)%20was%20a%20religious%20judge%20chosen%20by%20a%20merchant%20to%20act%20in%20his%20stead%2C%20for%20instance%20handling%20his%20lawsuits%20and%20acting%20as%20the%20merchant%E2%80%99s%20banker%20and%20postmaster.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20members%20of%20the%20first%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20were%20certainly%20familiar%20with%20the%20Latin%20term%20procurator.%20It%20referred%20to%20a%20man%20who%20acts%20as%20an%20agent%20of%20another%20man%2C%20with%20his%20consent.%20It%20referred%20to%20someone%20authorised%20to%20appear%20before%20a%20court%20to%20defend%20another%20person%20in%20a%20lawsuit%20or%20dispute.%20It%20was%20used%20as%20well%20to%20speak%20of%20an%20official%20(known%20as%20the%20%3Ci%3Eprocurador%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3Egeneral%3C%2Fi%3E)%20who%20took%20care%20of%20the%20property%20and%20wellbeing%20of%20the%20city%2C%20or%20who%20acted%20as%20a%20guardian%20of%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20poor%20(%3Ci%3Eprocurador%20de%20pobres%3C%2Fi%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20great%20refusal%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Le%C3%B3n%20parliament%20transformed%20the%20language%20of%20politics.%20It%20was%20also%20a%20great%20refusal%20of%20divine%2C%20absolute%20monarchy.%20This%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20was%20no%20gathering%20where%20monarchs%20waved%20the%20flags%20of%20courtly%20pomp%20to%20impress%20their%20subjects%20on%20bended%20knee.%20Against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20war%2C%20the%20old%20medieval%20custom%20of%20convening%20meetings%20such%20as%20the%20German%20%3Ci%3EHoftageand%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20English%20%3Ci%3Ewitanegemots%3C%2Fi%3E%20to%20swear%20fealty%20to%20a%20sovereign%E2%80%99s%20will%20was%20cast%20aside.%20Tough%20bargaining%20among%20conflicting%20social%20interests%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20monarch%20was%20the%20new%20custom.%20A%20parliamentary%20monarchy%20was%20born.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20parliament%20was%20held%20in%20the%20cloisters%20of%20the%20church%20of%20San%20Isidoro%2C%20named%20in%20honour%20of%20the%20good%20bishop%20of%20Seville%20famous%20for%20his%20maxim%20that%20only%20those%20who%20govern%20well%20are%20true%20monarchs.%20It%20produced%20up%20to%20fifteen%20decrees%20(the%20authenticity%20of%20several%20is%20disputed)%20that%20together%20amounted%20to%20something%20like%20a%20constitutional%20charter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20king%20promised%20that%20in%20matters%20of%20war%20and%20peace%2C%20pacts%20and%20treaties%20he%20would%20hereon%20consult%20and%20accept%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20bishops%2C%20nobles%20and%20%E2%80%98good%20men%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20towns.%20It%20was%20agreed%20that%20property%20and%20security%20of%20residence%20were%20inviolable.%20The%20representatives%20accepted%20that%20judicial%20proceedings%20and%20the%20laws%20they%20produced%20would%20be%20respected%3B%20and%20that%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20realm%20would%20be%20guided%2C%20wherever%20possible%2C%20by%20the%20good%20customs%20(%3Ci%3Emores%20bonos%3C%2Fi%3E)%20and%20general%20laws%20inherited%20from%20earlier%20times%20%E2%80%93%20the%20so-called%20Book%20or%20Liber%20Iudicorum%20from%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Visigoths.%20It%20was%20also%20agreed%20that%20there%20would%20be%20future%20assemblies%20of%20the%20king%20and%20the%20estates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20the%20profound%20historical%20and%20political%20significance%20of%20what%20happened%20in%20Le%C3%B3n.%20The%20assembly%20was%20the%20first%20recorded%20gathering%20of%20all%20three%20estates%3B%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20towns%20had%20hitherto%20been%20ignored%20in%20meetings%20convened%20by%20the%20monarchs%20of%20the%20region.%20We%20could%20say%20that%20the%20surprise%20inclusion%20of%20the%20towns%20was%20the%20beginning%20of%20many%20centuries%20of%20social%20and%20political%20struggle%20to%20equalize%20parliamentary%20representation%20%E2%80%93%20a%20struggle%20that%E2%80%99s%20nowadays%20still%20unfinished.%20But%20there%20was%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20assembly%20of%20representatives%20of%20the%20nobility%2C%20church%20and%20towns%20promised%20a%20new%20way%20of%20governing.%20The%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20method%20of%20handling%20power%20supposed%20that%20guarantees%20of%20fair%20play%20could%20foster%20political%20deals%20among%20conflicting%20interests%2C%20thus%20avoiding%20the%20use%20of%20naked%20force.%20In%20striking%20contrast%2C%20say%2C%20to%20ancient%20Athens%2C%20where%20citizens%20feared%20division%20and%20supposed%20that%20democracy%20required%20a%20unified%20sense%20of%20political%20community%2C%20the%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20rested%20on%20the%20opposite%20precept%3A%20on%20the%20inevitability%20of%20competing%20and%20conflicting%20interests.%20And%2C%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20the%20common%20good%2C%20the%20desirability%20of%20forging%20peaceful%20compromises%20among%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutting%20things%20more%20abstractly%2C%20we%20could%20say%20that%20the%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20redefined%20politics%20in%20four%20ways.%20Its%20embrace%20of%20representation%20had%20insurgent%2C%20disruptive%20effects.%20It%20sharpened%20people%E2%80%99s%20sense%20of%20the%20contingency%20or%20alterability%20of%20power%20relations.%20The%20cortesquestioned%20arbitrary%20power.%20It%20radicalised%20the%20old%20feudal%20notion%20of%20the%20contractual%20right%20of%20vassals%20to%20resist%20unjust%20treatment%20by%20their%20overlords.%20The%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20encouraged%20representatives%20to%20muster%20the%20courage%20to%20tell%20the%20king%20to%20go%20to%20hell.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%20before%20the%20age%20of%20party%20politics%2C%20the%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20also%20underlined%20the%20point%20that%20representatives%20don%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20share%20the%20same%20realities%20and%20that%20parliaments%20are%20therefore%20spaces%20in%20which%20reality%20itself%20becomes%20contestable%20and%20negotiable.%20The%20cortesanticipated%20Cervantes.%20It%20destroyed%20the%20metaphysics%20of%20reality%3A%20within%20its%20walls%2C%20representatives%20affirmed%20that%20things%20always%20have%20at%20least%20two%20sides-%20that%20the%20windmills%20of%20hard%20reality%20are%20inescapably%20shaped%20by%20interpretations%20that%20lend%20them%20significance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20had%20a%20third%20important%20effect%3A%20it%20offered%20the%20possibility%20of%20turning%20disagreements%20about%20reality%20into%20binding%20agreements%20in%20support%20of%20a%20common%20good.%20During%20these%20years%2C%20Spain%20was%20not%20yet%20a%20country.%20It%20was%20very%20much%20an%20invertebrate%20polity%2C%20to%20use%20the%20words%20of%20Ortega%20y%20Gasset%2C%20a%20space%20paralysed%20by%20social%20divisions%2C%20rebellions%20and%20threats%20of%20war.%20The%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20offered%20a%20positive%20alternative%3A%20combining%20social%20divisions%20into%20a%20more%20integrated%20polity%2C%20supported%20by%20people%20with%20straightened%20spines%3B%20a%20people%20bound%20together%20by%20their%20reliance%20upon%20parliamentary%20negotiations%20and%20agreed%20laws%20backed%20by%20the%20king.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20created%20the%20space%20for%20long-distance%20government.%20It%20widened%20its%20footprint.%20It%20improved%20the%20chances%20of%20reaching%20workable%20agreements%20among%20otherwise%20mutually%20hostile%20groups%20by%20limiting%20the%20number%20of%20decision-makers%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20were%20required%20to%20travel%20great%20distances.%20The%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20showed%20that%20representative%20governments%20could%20rule%20their%20subjects%20at%20arm%E2%80%99s%20length%20without%20losing%20their%20trust%20and%20consent.%20The%20government%20of%20large%20territories%20was%20possible%20exactly%20because%20the%20representatives%20involved%20in%20making%20decisions%20were%20entitled%20to%20snap%20at%20the%20heels%20of%20the%20monarch%2C%20to%20defend%20their%20respective%20interests%20in%20his%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30124400%2F1867-07-07_El_Museo_Universal_Vista_general_de_Le%25C3%25B3n.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30124400%2F1867-07-07_El_Museo_Universal_Vista_general_de_Le%25C3%25B3n.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30124400%2F1867-07-07_El_Museo_Universal_Vista_general_de_Le%25C3%25B3n-300x158.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30124400%2F1867-07-07_El_Museo_Universal_Vista_general_de_Le%25C3%25B3n-1024x538.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670622%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22631%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGeneral%20view%20of%20Leon%2C%20published%20in%201867.%20Photo%3A%20By%20Marcelo%20Paris%2C%20El%20Museo%20Universal%20XI%20via%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2C%20Public%20Domain%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELaboratories%20atop%20a%20graveyard%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20about%20the%20subsequent%20fate%20of%20the%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20of%20Le%C3%B3n%3F%20Encouraged%20by%20military%20victories%20over%20the%20Moors%2C%20the%20surviving%20evidence%20shows%20that%20the%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20managed%20to%20survive%20for%20several%20centuries.%20Long-distance%20government%20based%20on%20the%20consent%20of%20its%20subjects%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20fourteenth%20century%2C%20following%20a%20merger%20of%20the%20neighbouring%20kingdoms%20of%20Le%C3%B3n%20and%20Castile%2C%20the%20kingdom%E2%80%99s%20representatives%20enjoyed%20considerable%20powers.%20Their%20right%20of%20gathering%20and%20presenting%20petitions%2C%20and%20their%20insistence%20that%20agreements%20struck%20by%20the%20parliament%20were%20legally%20binding%2C%20became%20customary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConstitutional%20monarchy%20produced%20plenty%20of%20strife.%20The%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20was%20the%20site%20of%20intense%20bargaining%20about%20definitions%20of%20the%20welfare%20of%20the%20realm.%20Money%20was%20often%20the%20key%20cause%20of%20friction.%20Representatives%20constantly%20emphasised%20that%20kings%20were%20forbidden%20from%20manipulating%20coinage%20or%20levying%20extraordinary%20taxes%20without%20the%20explicit%20consent%20of%20all%20the%20estates.%20Before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20fourteenth%20century%2C%20there%20were%20times%20when%20the%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20reportedly%20demanded%20an%20audit%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20expenditure%2C%20even%20rebates%20on%20taxes%20that%20had%20already%20been%20paid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20Le%C3%B3n%20style%20of%20government%20proved%20geographically%20infectious.%20During%20the%20thirteenth%20century%2C%20parliaments%20spread%20from%20Le%C3%B3n%20and%20Castile%20to%20Aragon%2C%20Catalonia%2C%20Valencia%20and%20Navarre%2C%20to%20Sicily%20and%20Portugal%2C%20England%20and%20Ireland%2C%20and%20across%20the%20empires%20of%20Austria%20and%20Brandenburg.%20During%20the%20next%20two%20centuries%2C%20parliaments%20appeared%20in%20the%20large%20majority%20of%20German%20principalities%2C%20in%20Scotland%2C%20Denmark%2C%20Sweden%2C%20France%2C%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20Poland%20and%20Hungary.%20Nearly%20all%20these%20late%20medieval%20and%20early%20modern%20parliaments%20survived%20until%20the%20seventeenth%20and%20early%20eighteenth%20centuries.%20Despite%20the%20growth%20of%20absolutist%20states%2C%20which%20crushed%20the%20assemblies%20of%20Aragon%2C%20Catalonia%20and%20Valencia%2C%20many%20continued%20to%20function%20until%20the%20irruption%20of%20the%20French%20Revolution%20in%201789.%20The%20Navarrese%20cortes%2C%20the%20Swedish%20Riksdag%20and%20the%20Hungarian%20Di%C3%A9ta%20lasted%20into%20the%20nineteenth%20century.%20The%20powerful%20Estates%20of%20the%20Duchy%20of%20Mecklenburg%20survived%20intact%20until%201918.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20that%20time%2C%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20collapse%20of%20empires%20and%20a%20catastrophic%20world%20war%2C%20Europe%2C%20noted%20Tom%C3%A1%C5%A1%20Masaryk%2C%20had%20become%20%E2%80%98a%20laboratory%20atop%20a%20vast%20graveyard%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20laboratory%20of%20democracy%20in%20which%20most%20European%20parliaments%20were%20besieged%20by%20political%20parties%2C%20trade%20unions%2C%20suffragists%20and%20other%20citizens%20demanding%20universal%20suffrage.%20Many%20observers%20expected%20the%20dawn%20of%20parliamentary%20democracy%2C%20but%20as%20we%20know%2C%20the%20cruel%20opposite%20happened.%20The%20butterfly%20of%20parliamentary%20democracy%20became%20the%20caterpillar%20of%20arbitrary%20rule.%20The%20long%20democratic%20revolution%20unleashed%20by%20young%20King%20Alfonso%20IX%20had%20run%20its%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20another%20irony%3A%20just%20as%20%E2%80%98the%20people%E2%80%99%20mounted%20the%20stage%20of%20history%2C%20demanding%20%E2%80%98one%20person%2C%20one%20vote%E2%80%99%2C%20parliaments%20were%20racked%20by%20factional%20disputes%2C%20fierce%20backlashes%20and%20acts%20of%20violent%20sabotage.%20In%20countries%20like%20Yugoslavia%20and%20Romania%2C%20monarchs%20strangled%20parliaments.%20Military-backed%20dictators%20also%20savaged%20their%20parliaments%2C%20as%20happened%20in%20Pi%C5%82sudski%E2%80%99s%20Poland%20and%20Horthy%E2%80%99s%20Hungary.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3ETotalitarian%20rule%20triumphed%20in%20Italy%2C%20Germany%2C%20Russia%20and%20Spain%2C%20and%20also%20in%20China%2C%20which%20might%20otherwise%20have%20become%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20parliamentary%20republic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123046%2Fimage2-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22757%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123046%2Fimage2-1.jpeg%20757w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123046%2Fimage2-1-300x162.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670616%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22408%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAdmiral%20Mikl%C3%B3s%20Horthy%2C%20ruler%20of%20Hungary%20between%201919%20and%201944%2C%20greeted%20by%20city%20officials%20upon%20entering%20Budapest%2C%20November%201919%2C%20when%20in%20a%20fiery%20speech%20he%20accused%20the%20capital%E2%80%99s%20citizens%20of%20betraying%20Hungary%20by%20supporting%20Bolshevism.%20Photo%3A%20Unknown%20author%2C%20Public%20Domain%20via%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20these%20first%20decades%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20the%20downfall%20and%20disappearance%20of%20parliaments%20gathered%20pace.%20Politicians%20dressed%20in%20frock%20coats%20and%20top%20hats%20grew%20scared.%20The%20spirit%20of%20%E2%80%98dead%20bourgeois%20parliamentarism%E2%80%99%20(Lenin)%20fractured%20and%20paralysed%20parliaments.%20Governments%20rose%20and%20fell%20in%20quick%20succession.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Portugal%2C%20whose%20first%2015%20years%20of%20republican%20government%20had%20been%20marred%20by%20dozens%20of%20governments%2C%20eight%20presidents%20and%20countless%20attempted%20coups%2C%20the%20words%20of%20the%20new%20dictator%20Salazar%20blew%20like%20a%20winter%20wind%20across%20the%20whole%20continent%2C%20and%20well%20beyond.%20%E2%80%98So%20long%20as%20there%20is%20not%20some%20retrograde%20movement%20in%20political%20evolution%2C%E2%80%99%20he%20said%20in%201934%2C%20%E2%80%98I%20am%20convinced%20that%20within%2020%20years%20there%20will%20be%20no%20legislative%20assemblies%20left%20in%20Europe.%E2%80%99%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERump%20parliaments%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESalazar%E2%80%99s%20wishful%20prediction%20almost%20came%20true.%20By%201941%2C%20there%20were%20only%2011%20parliamentary%20democracies%20left%20on%20our%20planet.%20Only%20three%20survived%20in%20Europe%3A%20Britain%2C%20Sweden%2C%20and%20Switzerland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistorians%20and%20political%20scientists%20tell%20us%20the%20good%20news%20that%20after%20World%20War%20Two%20parliamentary%20government%20made%20a%20stupendous%20political%20comeback.%20The%20not-so-good%20news%20is%20that%20the%20long%20post-1945%20renaissance%20of%20parliaments%20is%20today%20losing%20momentum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20writing%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20parliaments.%20We%E2%80%99re%20living%20through%20times%20in%20which%20parliaments%20are%20again%20plagued%20by%20legitimacy%20and%20performance%20problems.%20We%20need%20to%20pay%20special%20attention%20to%20this%20new%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20aren%E2%80%99t%20backsliding%20to%20former%20times%2C%20say%2C%20to%20the%20catastrophes%20of%20the%201920s%20and%201930s.%20We%20aren%E2%80%99t%20even%20facing%20the%20kind%20of%20overnight%20emergencies%20that%20gripped%20Spain%20on%20February%2023rd%201981%20%E2%80%93the%20moment%20described%20with%20great%20precision%20in%20Javier%20Cercas%E2%80%99s%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomsbury.com%2Fau%2Fanatomy-of-a-moment-9781408822104%5C%22%3E%20%3Ci%3EAnatom%C3%ADa%20de%20un%20instante%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%2C%20in%20a%20hail%20of%20bullets%2C%20a%20frightened%20Cortes%20fell%20to%20the%20floor%20and%20was%20held%20hostage%20for%20six%20hours%20by%20%3Ci%3Egolpistas%3C%2Fi%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20recent%20events%20in%20Bolivia%2C%20Burkina%20Faso%2C%20Mali%2C%20Myanmar%2C%20Sudan%2C%20Thailand%20and%20Yemen%20suggest%20that%20armies%20are%20still%20enemies%20of%20parliaments%2C%20but%20the%20main%20forces%20threatening%20the%20integrity%20of%20parliaments%20are%20nowadays%20different.%20They%20seem%20more%20banal.%20Their%20rhythm%20is%20different.%20But%20these%20new%20threats%2C%20if%20left%20untreated%2C%20are%20bound%20in%20the%20long%20run%20to%20destroy%20parliaments%20as%20effectively%20as%20happened%20a%20century%20ago%20in%20the%20heartlands%20of%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F05165126%2FScreenshot-2023-08-05-at-4.50.42-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F05165126%2FScreenshot-2023-08-05-at-4.50.42-PM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F05165126%2FScreenshot-2023-08-05-at-4.50.42-PM-300x158.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F05165126%2FScreenshot-2023-08-05-at-4.50.42-PM-1024x538.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-666806%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20a%20protest%20in%20Niger%E2%80%99s%20capital%20Niamey%20against%20the%20coup%20%3Cspan%3Ed%E2%80%99%C3%A9tat%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20Photo%3A%20Screengrab%20via%20Twitter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20are%20these%20new%20sources%20of%20ruination%3F%20Most%20obviously%2C%20rising%20tides%20of%20reputational%20damage%20are%20lapping%20around%20parliament%E2%80%99s%20doorsteps.%20Cynicism%2C%20grumbling%2C%20ressentiment%20and%20angry%20citizens%E2%80%99%20protests%20are%20becoming%20commonplace.%20On%20an%20already%20overheated%20planet%2C%20parliaments%20are%20said%20to%20be%20hot%20air%20chambers%2C%20mere%20talk%20shops%2C%20fabricators%20of%20unreality%2C%20quarrelsome%20kindergartens%2C%20warehouses%20of%20division%2C%20irrelevance%20and%20incompetence.%20Parliaments%20are%20the%20butt%20of%20bitter%20jokes.%20My%20Irish%20working%20class%20father%20%E2%80%93%20who%20knew%20something%20of%20the%201605%20Gunpowder%20Treason%20Plot%20by%20supporters%20of%20Catholic%20Spain%20to%20blow%20up%20England%E2%80%99s%20House%20of%20Lords%20%E2%80%93%20liked%20to%20say%20that%20only%20one%20man%20ever%20entered%20parliament%20with%20honest%20intentions%2C%20and%20that%20was%20Guy%20Fawkes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETomfoolery%20and%20contempt%20for%20politicians%20hurt%20and%20harm%20parliaments%20from%20the%20outside%2C%20but%20just%20as%20worrying%20are%20the%20forces%20of%20decadence%20within%20the%20walls%20of%20parliaments.%20There%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20the%20grandstanding%2C%20slam-bang%20rancour%2C%20misogyny%20and%20cluelessness%20of%20more%20than%20a%20few%20politicians.%20Or%20the%20%E2%80%98dead%20hand%20of%20party%20discipline%E2%80%99%2C%20as%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com.au%2FFire-Ashes-Success-Failure-Politics%2Fdp%2F0674725999%2Fref%3Dasc_df_0674725999%2F%3Ftag%3Dgoogleshopdsk-22%26linkCode%3Ddf0%26hvadid%3D341744884947%26hvpos%3D%26hvnetw%3Dg%26hvrand%3D14777827810864353864%26hvpone%3D%26hvptwo%3D%26hvqmt%3D%26hvdev%3Dc%26hvdvcmdl%3D%26hvlocint%3D%26hvlocp%5C%22%3E%20Michael%20Ignatieff%3C%2Fa%3E%20put%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParliaments%20are%20materially%20corrupted%20by%20the%20combined%20forces%20of%20lobbyists%2C%20dark%20money%20merchants%20and%20revolving%20doors.%20In%20Washington%20DC%2C%20this%20tangled%20complex%20of%20government%20agencies%2C%20think%20tanks%2C%20corporations%2C%20academics%20and%20lobbyists%20with%20big%20toes%20in%20the%20lawmaking%20world%20of%20legislatures%20is%20known%20(for%20obvious%20reasons)%20as%20%E2%80%98the%20blob%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomething%20similar%20is%20happening%20in%20the%20European%20Union%20where%2C%20in%20Brussels%20alone%2C%20nearly%2012%2C000%20organisations%20on%20the%20current%20voluntary%20EU%20lobby%20register%20declare%20that%20each%20year%20they%20spend%20a%20total%20of%20around%201.8%20billion%20euros%20on%20their%20craft.%20At%20least%207%2C500%20organisations%20operate%20without%20scrutiny%20in%20and%20around%20the%20European%20Parliament.%20Whatever%20is%20thought%20of%20the%20ethics%20of%20lobbying%2C%20the%20fact%20is%20government%20by%20moonlight%20is%20a%20growing%20problem%20in%20every%20parliamentary%20democracy.%20Mandatory%20accountability%20registers%20and%20comprehensive%20integrity%20checks%20to%20prevent%20%E2%80%98Qatargate%E2%80%99%20corruption%20scandals%20and%20to%20ensure%20ethical%20fair%20play%20among%20lobbyists%20are%20typically%20in%20short%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20lower%20chamber%20Lok%20Sabha%20is%20the%20nightmare%20instance%20of%20what%20happens%20when%20lobbying%2C%20dirty%20money%2C%20shady%20deals%2C%20blackmail%20and%20criminality%20get%20the%20upper%20hand.%20In%20what%E2%80%99s%20known%20as%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20democracy%2C%20more%20money%20is%20spent%20on%20elections%20than%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20even%20though%20average%20per%20capita%20income%20is%20only%203%25%20of%20US%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20no%20state%20funding%20for%20political%20parties%20and%20no%20proper%20regulation%20of%20party%20finances.%2075%25%20of%20party%20funding%20comes%20from%20%E2%80%98unknown%E2%80%99%20sources%2C%20including%20tax-free%20electoral%20bonds%20bought%20from%20the%20state-owned%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20and%20anonymously%20deposited%20into%20the%20parties%E2%80%99%20registered%20bank%20accounts.%20An%20estimated%20one-quarter%20of%20total%20election%20campaign%20expenditure%20goes%20directly%20to%20voters%20as%20cash%20and%20gifts.%20The%20upshot%20is%20that%20in%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20India%2C%20parliament%20becomes%20a%20place%20of%20business%20deals%2C%20organised%20crime%20and%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.panmacmillan.com%2Fauthors%2Fdebasish-roy-chowdhury%2Fto-kill-a-democracy%2F9789390742806%5C%22%3Eresort%20politics%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20(an%20Indian%20specialty%3A%20party%20bosses%20buying%20off%20recalcitrant%20lawmakers%20in%20luxury%20hotel%20hideaways).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%202019%20elections%2C%20unsurprisingly%2C%2043%25%20of%20MPs%20in%20the%20directly%20elected%20Lok%20Sabha%20had%20declared%20criminal%20cases%20against%20them%20(self-declaration%20is%20an%20election%20rule)%3B%2029%25%20confessed%20to%20%E2%80%98serious%E2%80%99%20criminal%20charges%2C%20which%20include%20murder%2C%20attempted%20murder%2C%20kidnapping%2C%20rape%20and%20other%20crimes%20against%20women.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1-300x146.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1-1024x498.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670619%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22584%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20new%20parliament%20building.%20Photo%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20case%20shows%20how%2C%20in%20the%20name%20of%20democracy%2C%20parliaments%20can%20slowly%20degrade%20into%20mere%20meetings%20of%20more%20or%20less%20corrupted%20souls.%20The%20old%20saying%20that%20the%20word%20politics%20comes%20from%20poly%2C%20meaning%20many%2C%20and%20ticks%2C%20meaning%20bloodsucking%20parasites%2C%20then%20applies%20with%20a%20cruel%20vengeance.%20The%20decadence%20is%20perfected%20when%20parliaments%20fall%20victim%20to%20executive%20capture%2C%20to%20what%20Thomas%20Jefferson%20originally%20called%20%E2%80%98elective%20despotism%E2%80%99.%20In%20more%20than%20a%20few%20of%20today%E2%80%99s%20democracies%2C%20the%20centre%20of%20gravity%20of%20government%20is%20shifting%20from%20parliaments%20towards%20media-spun%20presidential%20rule.%20Take%20note%20of%20how%20growing%20numbers%20of%20political%20oligarchs%20do%20everything%20they%20can%20to%20prorogue%20their%20parliaments%2C%20take%20decisions%20without%20consultation%2C%20all%20the%20while%20ignoring%20calls%20for%20accountability.%20They%20boast%2C%20contradict%20themselves%20and%20lie%20with%20impunity.%20Their%20media%20performances%20are%20reality%20shows.%20Excrement%20without%20nutrient%20%E2%80%93%20commonly%20called%20bullshit%20%E2%80%93%20is%20their%20specialty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20this%20colonisation%20of%20parliaments%20happens%2C%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20L%C3%A9on%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20is%20replaced%20by%20the%20mantra%20of%20Charles%20de%20Gaulle%3A%20that%20politics%20is%20much%20too%20serious%20a%20matter%20to%20be%20left%20to%20time-wasting%2C%20dithering%20politicians.%20The%20trend%20resembles%20a%20slow-motion%20coup%20d%E2%80%99%C3%A9tat.%20It%20is%20backed%20by%20tactics%20such%20as%20government%20whipping%2C%20gag%20orders%2C%20gerrymandering%20and%20voter%20deregistration%2C%20emergency%20rule%2C%20compulsory%20budget%20limits%2C%20and%20the%20punishment%20of%20dissenting%20members.%20There%20are%20also%20kickbacks%20and%20favours%20and%2C%20lest%20we%20underestimate%2C%20sly%20efforts%20to%20outflank%20parliaments%20and%20silence%20their%20committees%20with%20the%20help%20of%20hand-picked%2C%20loyal%20bureaucrats%2C%20journalists%2C%20judges%20and%20other%20high%20officials%2C%20as%20Donald%20J.%20Trump%20attempted%20during%20his%20post-2016%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThings%20grow%20worse%20when%20populist%20parties%20and%20their%20demagogues%20get%20their%20paws%20on%20the%20levers%20of%20government.%20Populism%20accelerates%20the%20transition%20to%20elective%20despotism.%20Populists%20like%20Erdo%C4%9Fan%2C%20Kais%20Saied%2C%20Vu%C4%8Di%C4%87%2C%20L%C3%B3pez%20Obrador%20and%20Kaczy%C5%84ski%20favour%20executive%20rule.%20They%20have%20a%20taste%20for%20prorogued%20legislatures%2C%20or%20what%20the%20English%20used%20to%20call%20rump%20parliaments%3A%20chambers%20that%20resemble%20chunks%20of%20rotting%20meat%20infected%20with%20maggots%2C%20parliamentary%20representatives%20who%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20people%20do%20little%20more%20than%20serve%20their%20executive%20masters%20on%20bended%20knees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThings%20grow%20much%20worse%20when%20populist%20governments%20de-regulate%2C%20privatise%20and%20commodify%20public%20services.%20When%20neo-liberalism%20gets%20the%20upper%20hand%2C%20parliaments%20are%20blindsided.%20They%20become%20complicit%20in%20the%20growth%20of%20what%20should%20be%20called%20democracy%20exclusion%20zones%3A%20self-regulating%20banks%2C%20lawless%20tax%20havens%2C%20secret%20military-industrial%20complexes%2C%20and%20buccaneer%20data-harvesting%20media%20corporations%20which%20elude%20parliamentary%20scrutiny%20and%20legislative%20restraint.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F17121459%2FRecep_Tayyip_Erdogan_2020-03-05_02.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F17121459%2FRecep_Tayyip_Erdogan_2020-03-05_02.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F17121459%2FRecep_Tayyip_Erdogan_2020-03-05_02-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F17121459%2FRecep_Tayyip_Erdogan_2020-03-05_02-1024x683.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-653369%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERecep%20Tayyip%20Erdogan.%20Photo%3A%20Mikhail%20Klimentyev%2FRussian%20Presidential%20Press%20And%20Information%20Office%2FTASS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFightbacks%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20of%20the%20future%20of%20parliaments%3F%20Do%20they%20have%20a%20future%3F%20When%20thinking%20about%20these%20various%20decadent%20trends%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20tempting%20to%20conclude%20that%20the%20post-1945%20renaissance%20of%20parliaments%20is%20coming%20to%20an%20end.%20We%20may%20even%20think%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20already%20entering%20the%20age%20of%20phantom%20parliaments%20in%20which%20legislatures%20in%20more%20than%20a%20few%20countries%20are%20simultaneously%20real%20and%20not%20real%2C%20form%20without%20much%20content.%20In%20these%20make-believe%20spaces%2C%20elected%20representatives%20claim%20to%20serve%20the%20people%2C%20even%20though%20they%20are%20of%20limited%20or%20no%20significance%20to%20the%20people%20in%20whose%20name%20they%20pass%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20shift%20to%20phantom%20parliaments%20and%20executive%20rule%20may%20be%20welcomed%20in%20some%20quarters%2C%20but%20before%20the%20cava%20is%20poured%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20consider%20the%20countertrends%2C%20and%20the%20reasons%20why%2C%20in%20these%20years%20of%20the%2021st%20century%2C%20the%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20model%20of%20government%20remains%20indispensable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20politics%2C%20nothing%20is%20set%20in%20stone.%20To%20speak%20in%20quantum%20terms%2C%20contemporary%20parliaments%20are%20in%20a%20state%20of%20superposition.%20Just%20as%20the%20fate%20of%20Schr%C3%B6dinger%E2%80%99s%20cat%20in%20a%20box%20was%20undecidable%2C%20so%20are%20parliaments%20today%20suspended%20unpredictably%20between%20alternative%20outcomes.%20Fightbacks%20are%20possible.%20They%20are%20necessary.%20Remarkably%2C%20renewals%20are%20happening%20at%20multiple%20points%20on%20our%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsider%20Denmark%E2%80%99s%20Folketinget%3A%20in%20meetings%20called%20consultations%20(%3Ci%3Esamr%C3%A5d%3C%2Fi%3E)%2C%20its%20powerful%20European%20Affairs%20Committee%20regularly%20grills%20ministers%20in%20real-time%20during%20sessions%20of%20the%20Council%20of%20the%20European%20Union%20in%20Brussels%20and%20Luxembourg.%20The%20National%20Assembly%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20Korea%20has%20signed%20off%20on%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20comprehensive%20laws%20against%20verbal%20abuse%20and%20bullying%20(%3Ci%3Egapjil%3C%2Fi%3E)%20by%20family-run%20conglomerates%20and%20other%20powerful%20organisations.%20Romania%E2%80%99s%20parliament%20is%20now%20digitally%20fed%20citizens%E2%80%99%20suggestions%20and%20complaints%20with%20the%20help%20of%20ION%2C%20a%20smart%20robot%2C%20say%20the%20wags%2C%20designed%20to%20improve%20the%20%E2%80%98intelligence%E2%80%99%20of%20politicians.%20Proposals%20are%20afoot%20in%20the%20German%20Bundestag%20to%20receive%20non-binding%20reports%20from%20lottery-selected%20citizens%E2%80%99%20assemblies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParliaments%20are%20also%20heavily%20preoccupied%20with%20time%20past%20and%20time%20future.%20The%20Welsh%20legislature%20regularly%20consults%20with%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20Future%20Generations%20Commissioner.%20With%20eyes%20on%20the%20unmade%20future%2C%20the%20European%20Parliament%20has%20drafted%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20first%20AI%20Act.%20New%20Zealand%E2%80%99s%20(Aotearoa%E2%80%99s)%20parliament%20has%20granted%20ecosystems%20%E2%80%98the%20rights%2C%20powers%2C%20duties%20and%20liabilities%20of%20a%20legal%20person%E2%80%99.%20The%20cross-border%20Nordic%20network%20of%20Sami%20parliaments%2C%20the%20S%C3%A1mediggi%20is%20a%20case%20of%20interparliamentary%20cooperation%2C%20featuring%20consultative%20bodies%20whose%20brief%20is%20to%20promote%20and%20preserve%20indigenous%20self-determination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30122644%2Fimage1-3.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30122644%2Fimage1-3.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30122644%2Fimage1-3-300x152.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30122644%2Fimage1-3-1024x519.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670611%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22608%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENorway%E2%80%99s%20S%C3%A1mi%20Parliament%2C%20the%20representative%20body%20for%20people%20of%20S%C3%A1mi%20heritage%2C%20opened%20in%20October%201989.%20Photo%3A%20Illustratedjc%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%203.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWatchdog%20parliaments%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20are%20we%20to%20make%20good%20sense%20of%20this%20new%20wave%20of%20experiments%3F%20My%20suggestion%20is%20to%20see%20them%20as%20points%20on%20a%20larger%20canvas%2C%20single%20performances%20in%20a%20grand%20carnival%20of%20parliamentary%20efforts%20to%20rejuvenate%20the%20%3Ci%3Ecortes%3C%2Fi%3E%20spirit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShadows%20are%20certainly%20falling%20on%20too%20many%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20parliaments.%20But%20these%20innovations%20are%20the%20first%20signs%20of%20a%20dawn%20of%20renewal.%20They%20breathe%20new%20life%20into%20old%20institutions%20originally%20designed%20to%20make%20binding%20agreements%20by%20lawmakers%20acting%20on%20behalf%20of%20different%20social%20interests%2C%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20commonwealth.%20More%20obviously%2C%20these%20parliamentary%20experiments%20are%20today%20doing%20what%20parliaments%20did%20for%20over%20eight%20centuries%3A%20representing%20the%20claims%20and%20interests%20of%20the%20represented%20%E2%80%93%20and%20they%20remind%20us%20that%20parliamentary%20representation%20is%2C%20by%20definition%2C%20tricky%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPopulists%20and%20demagogues%20be%20warned%3A%20representation%20isn%E2%80%99t%20a%20simple%2C%20face-to-face%20contract%20between%20a%20representative%20and%20an%20imaginary%20People%20or%20Nation.%20Representation%20isn%E2%80%99t%20mimesis.%20It%20has%20a%20vicarious%2C%20fiduciary%20quality%2C%20and%20this%20means%20that%20when%20voters%20choose%20a%20representative%2C%20representation%20is%20as%20much%20an%20ending%20as%20it%20is%20a%20beginning.%20Representation%20is%20an%20open-ended%20process%20contingent%20upon%20the%20assent%2C%20disappointment%20and%20displeasure%20of%20the%20represented.%20When%20representatives%20underperform%2C%20or%20fail%20on%20too%20many%20fronts%2C%20they%20are%20sent%20to%20hell%20in%20a%20handbasket.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20principles%20of%20representation%2C%20traceable%20to%20the%20L%C3%A9on%20cortes%20convened%20by%20Alfonso%20IX%2C%20are%20most%20definitely%20alive%20and%20kicking%20in%20the%20new%20parliamentary%20experiments.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20textbooks%20still%20tell%20us%20that%20the%20prime%20task%20of%20parliaments%20is%20to%20represent%20the%20interests%20of%20citizens%20by%20means%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections.%20But%20there%E2%80%99s%20an%20error%20within%20the%20textbooks%3A%20if%20we%20look%20more%20closely%20at%20what%20today%E2%80%99s%20smart%2C%20activist%20parliaments%20are%20actually%20doing%2C%20we%20see%20a%20departure%20of%20great%20historical%20significance%20ignored%20by%20the%20textbooks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParliaments%20aren%E2%80%99t%20just%20chambers%20or%20%E2%80%98little%20rooms%E2%80%99%20where%20elected%20politicians%20represent%20their%20constituents.%20In%20our%20age%20of%20monitory%20democracy%2C%20legislatures%20are%20becoming%20watchdog%20parliaments.%20In%20the%20name%20of%20the%20common%20good%2C%20they%20blow%20whistles%2C%20sound%20alarms%2C%20warn%20of%20wicked%20problems%20and%20pass%20laws%20to%20push%20back%20or%20ban%20arbitrary%20exercises%20of%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30125154%2F1078px-Eduskunta_istuntosali.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221078%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30125154%2F1078px-Eduskunta_istuntosali.jpg%201078w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30125154%2F1078px-Eduskunta_istuntosali-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30125154%2F1078px-Eduskunta_istuntosali-1024x684.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670628%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20House%20of%20Parliament%20in%20Finland.%20Representative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20Tiina%20Tuukkanen%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20contrast%20with%20parliaments%20of%20yesteryear%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20clearer.%20The%20first-ever%20cortes%20was%20born%20of%20military%20conquest.%20Parliaments%20of%20the%20more%20recent%20past%20were%20too%20often%20the%20castles%20of%20the%20aristocracy%2C%20bourgeois%20mansions%2C%20parlours%20of%20male%20privilege%2C%20and%20engines%20of%20empire.%20By%20contrast%2C%20today%E2%80%99s%20watchdog%20parliaments%2C%20when%20they%20work%20well%2C%20stand%20against%20conquest%20in%20all%20its%20various%20forms.%20Especially%20when%20generously%20resourced%2C%20watchdog%20parliaments%20specialise%20in%20the%20public%20scrutiny%20and%20restraint%20of%20predatory%20power.%20They%20stand%20against%20foolish%20governments%20that%20abuse%20their%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWatchdog%20parliaments%20snap%20the%20chains%20of%20majority%20rule%2C%20the%20blind%20worship%20of%20numbers%2C%20by%20granting%20voices%20and%20rights%20to%20minorities%20excluded%20from%20high%20politics.%20These%20parliaments%20alter%20our%20shared%20sense%20of%20time.%20They%20extend%20the%20franchise%20to%20endangered%20species%2C%20wronged%20ancestors%20and%20future%20generations.%20In%20opposition%2C%20say%2C%20to%20predatory%20corporations%2C%20greedy%20banks%20and%20rogue%20mining%20companies%2C%20watchdog%20parliaments%20protect%20and%20promote%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20democratic%20game.%20Not%20to%20be%20underestimated%20is%20the%20way%20they%20strive%20to%20tackle%20long-term%20problems%2C%20currently%20sidelined%20by%20the%20short-term%20mentality%20of%20election%20cycles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWatchdog%20parliaments%20are%20more%20than%20the%20guardians%20of%20electoral%20integrity.%20As%20champions%20of%20the%20public%20monitoring%20of%20power%2C%20they%20target%20complex%2C%20difficult%2C%20wicked%20problems.%20Their%20job%20is%20to%20find%20just%20solutions%20for%20matters%20such%20as%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20tax%20havens%2C%20polluted%20environments%2C%20pestilences%2C%20the%20plight%20of%20stateless%20peoples%2C%20the%20unregulated%20arms%20trade%20and%20unending%20wars%20of%20attrition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20performing%20these%20functions%2C%20paradoxically%2C%20watchdog%20parliaments%20push%20beyond%20the%20%E2%80%98parliamentary%20road%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20fetish%20of%20periodic%20elections.%20They%20help%20redefine%20democracy%20and%20give%20it%20teeth.%20Electoral%20democracy%20becomes%20monitory%20democracy.%20Democracy%20comes%20to%20mean%20nothing%20less%20than%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%2C%20but%20also%20something%20much%20more%3A%20citizens%E2%80%99%20freedom%20from%20predatory%20power%20in%20all%20its%20ugly%20forms%2C%20including%20our%20reckless%20relationship%20with%20the%20Earth%20on%20which%20we%20dwell.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrue%2C%20the%20new%20watchdog%20parliaments%20are%20fragile.%20They%20function%20without%20much%20intellectual%20support.%20No%20grand%20political%20theories%20of%20the%20order%20of%20Fran%C3%A7ois%20Guizot%E2%80%99s%20lectures%20on%20the%20origins%20of%20representative%20government%20in%20the%20early%201820s%2C%20or%20John%20Stuart%20Mill%E2%80%99s%20Considerations%20on%20Representative%20Government%20(1861)%20have%20come%20to%20their%20defence.%20They%20lack%20guidebooks%20and%20operating%20manuals.%20This%20is%20to%20say%20that%20watchdog%20parliaments%20enjoy%20no%20scholarly%20fanfare%20and%20no%20historical%20guarantees%20of%20success.%20Except%20for%20future%20historians%2C%20their%20chances%20of%20survival%20are%20unknown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20thing%20that%E2%80%99s%20certain%20is%20that%20the%20spirit%20of%20these%20watchdog%20parliaments%20%E2%80%93%20the%20spirit%20of%20young%20King%20Alfonso%20IX%20%E2%80%93%20is%20the%20grit%20we%20humans%20are%20going%20to%20need%20as%20we%20struggle%20to%20deal%20wisely%2C%20equitably%2C%20democratically%20with%20the%20rich%20opportunities%20and%20cascading%20dangers%20of%20our%20troubled%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EAn%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurozine.com%2Fwhy-parliaments%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Eearlier%20version%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20of%20this%20appeared%20in%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurozine.com%5C%22%3EEurozine%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%20(Vienna)%20on%20August%207%2C%202023.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJohn%20Keane%20is%20Professor%20of%20Politics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Sydney.%20His%20latest%20book%20is%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Shortest%20History%20of%20Democracy%3Cem%3E%20(Picador%20Macmillan%2C%20Delhi%202023).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693380956000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123614%2Fsan-isidoro.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhat-is-the-future-of-parliaments-in-our-troubled-century%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20is%20the%20text%20of%20the%20keynote%20address%20delivered%20by%20John%20Keane%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20King%20Felipe%20VI%2C%20at%20the%20launch%20of%20the%20EU%20Global%20Project%20to%20Strengthen%20the%20Capacity%20of%20Parliaments%2C%20L%C3%A9on%2C%20Spain%2C%20June%2030%2C%202023.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhat-is-the-future-of-parliaments-in-our-troubled-century%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22United%20States%20says%20seeking%20more%20'predictable'%20business%20environment%20in%20China%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22publish