It%20is%20these%20cables%20that%20make%20global%20communications%20between%20India%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20possible%20in%20the%20digital%20age.%20This%2C%20it%20finds%2C%20is%20fuelling%20and%20helping%20private%20companies%20that%20sell%20powerful%20surveillance%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20FT%20identifies%20include%20Indian%20providers%20such%20as%20Vehere%2C%20%E2%80%9Cas%20well%20as%20less%20well%20known%20Israeli%20groups%20like%20Cognyte%20or%20Septier.%E2%80%9D%20The%20profile%20and%20track-record%20of%20some%20of%20these%20companies%20have%20raised%20serious%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeptier%20was%20among%20companies%20termed%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpotentially%20irresponsible%20proliferator%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20Atlantic%20Council%20in%202021%2C%20which%20it%20meant%20as%20those%20companies%20%E2%80%9Cwilling%20to%20accept%20or%20ignore%20the%20risk%20that%20their%20products%20will%20bolster%20the%20capabilities%20of%20client%20governments%20that%20might%20wish%20to%20threaten%20US%2FNato%20national%20security%20or%20harm%20marginalised%20populations%E2%80%9D.%20Septier%20called%20this%20%E2%80%9Cpure%20speculation%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20time%2C%20as%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20case%20is%20unusual%20and%20an%20exception%20to%20most%20other%20democracies%2C%20as%20it%20requires%20%E2%80%9Ctelecom%20companies%20to%20install%20surveillance%20equipment%20at%20subsea%20cable%20landing%20stations%20and%20data%20centres%20that%20is%20approved%20by%20the%20government%20as%20a%20condition%20of%20operation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Snowden%20tapes%20created%20a%20storm%2C%20revealing%20how%20intelligence%20agencies%20in%20the%20US%20and%20UK%20were%20engaged%20in%20mass%20surveillance%20via%20backdoor%20arrangements%2C%20telecom%20companies%20have%20pushed%20back%20on%20government%20pressure%20%E2%80%9Cto%20install%20official%20backdoors%20providing%20unfettered%20access%20to%20customer%20data.%E2%80%9D%20They%20have%20preferred%20to%20demand%20a%20court-approved%20warrant%20for%20targeted%20interception%2C%20as%20and%20when%20governments%20have%20made%20requests%20for%20surveillance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20finds%20itself%20amongst%20countries%20like%20Uganda%20and%20Rwanda%2C%20who%20have%20similar%20interception%20laws.%20But%2C%20remarks%20FT%2C%20the%20scale%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20telecoms%20usage%20has%20zoomed%20in%20recent%20years.%20Projections%20of%20wireless%20data%20usage%20are%20up%20%E2%80%9Cfrom%20an%20average%20of%201.24GB%20per%20person%20a%20month%20in%202018%20to%20over%2014GB.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20companies%20we%20keep%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeptier%20is%20an%20Israel-based%20company.%20Founded%20in%202000%2C%20has%20sold%20its%20lawful%20interception%20technology%20to%20telecoms%20groups%20including%20Mukesh%20Ambani%E2%80%99s%20Reliance%20Jio%2C%20the%20Vodafone%20Idea%20Indian%20joint%20venture%20and%20Singapore%E2%80%99s%20Singtel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael-based%20Cognyte%2C%20is%20cited%20as%20another%20leading%20provider%20of%20surveillance%20products%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVehere%2C%20jointly%20headquartered%20in%20India%20and%20the%20US%2C%20is%20also%20mentioned%20as%20a%20company%20relevant%20in%20this%20context.%20It%20advertises%20its%20%E2%80%9Cstate%20of%20the%20art%20monitoring%20solution%E2%80%9D%20that%20helps%20telecom%20companies%20%E2%80%9Cfulfil%20their%20legal%20obligation%20to%20intercept%20calls%20and%20data%20while%20maintaining%20maximum%20privacy%20protection%E2%80%9D%2C%20says%20FT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20contacted%20the%20government%20of%20India%2C%20Cognyte%2C%20Vehere%2C%20Reliance%20Jio%20and%20Singtel%20for%20comments%2C%20but%20says%20they%20did%20not%20respond.%20Vodafone%20Idea%20said%20it%20%E2%80%9Cremains%20strictly%20compliant%20to%20licensing%20conditions%20mandated%20by%20%5Bthe%5D%20government%20of%20India%20and%20the%20prevailing%20regulations%20in%20force%20at%20any%20given%20time%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBroader%20concerns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConcerns%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20surveillance%20regime%20have%20multiplied%20since%20reports%20about%20India%20deploying%20the%20Pegasus%20spyware%20of%20Israeli%20group%20NSO%2C%20%E2%80%9Ctriggering%20a%20political%20scandal%20when%20the%20hacking%20tool%20was%20found%20on%20the%20phones%20of%20journalists%20and%20activists%20in%202019%20and%202021.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202021%2C%2016%20international%20news%20organisations%20including%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20French%20media%20non-profit%20Forbidden%20Stories%20and%20Amnesty%20International%20c%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Frevealed-how-the-wire-partners-cracked-pegasus-project-implications-india%5C%22%3Eame%20together%20to%20expose%20the%20use%20of%20this%20spyware%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20the%20NSO%20Group%20said%20it%20only%20sold%20to%20governments%20%E2%80%93%20was%20used%20across%20the%20world%2C%20including%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20personal%20data%20protection%20bill%20passed%20in%20this%20monsoon%20session%20of%20Parliament%20has%20been%20criticised%20for%20being%20one%20that%20protects%20governments%20from%20scrutiny%20and%20not%20citizens%2C%20providing%20legal%20cover%20for%20surveillance.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-lies-beneath-the-pr-blitz-on-the-new-data-protection-act%5C%22%3ECritics%20and%20activists%20say%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20government%E2%80%99s%20favourite%20catchphrase%20%E2%80%98as%20may%20be%20prescribed%E2%80%99%20is%20the%20highlight%20of%20this%20DPDP%20Act.%20It%20has%20been%20used%2028%20times%20in%20a%2021-page%20Act%20with%2044%20sections.%20The%20ambiguity%20has%20been%20kept%20so%20that%20the%20government%20can%20take%20arbitrary%20decisions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693380610000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F21193814%2Fsurveillance.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Findias-laws-create-dangerous-backdoor-for-surveillance-companies-govt-surveillance-ft%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20finds%20itself%20amongst%20countries%20like%20Uganda%20and%20Rwanda%2C%20as%20far%20as%20laws%20allowing%20for%20interception%20of%20communication%20goes.%20Most%20companies%20globally%20ask%20governments%20for%20a%20%E2%80%98court-approved%20warrant%20for%20targeted%20interception%E2%80%99.%20Not%20so%2C%20here.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Findias-laws-create-dangerous-backdoor-for-surveillance-companies-govt-surveillance-ft%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shah%20Rukh%20Khan%20offers%20prayers%20at%20Vaishnodevi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693380563000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103202442%2Cimgsize-20942.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fshah-rukh-khan-spotted-at-vaishnodevi-temple-before-the-music-launch-of-jawan%2Farticleshow%2F103202484.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103202484.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EShah%20Rukh%20Khan%20is%20seeking%20some%20divine%20intervention%20before%20the%20release%20of%20his%20upcoming%20film%20Jawan%2C%20he%20was%20spotted%20at%20Katra%20walking%20up%20the%20path%20to%20the%20Mata%20Vaishnodevi%20temple.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fshah-rukh-khan-spotted-at-vaishnodevi-temple-before-the-music-launch-of-jawan%2Farticleshow%2F103202484.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Now%20Needs%20A%20Strategic%20Vision%20For%20Space%2C%20Boost%20Space%20Tech%3A%20Experts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESix%20decades%20after%20its%20first%20rocket%20launch%2C%20India%2C%20with%20the%20success%20of%20its%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%20now%20has%20a%20surer%20footing%20in%20the%20field%20of%20space%20exploration%20and%20technology.%20But%20now%2C%20experts%20say%20is%20time%20the%20country%20came%20up%20with%20a%20national%20strategic%20vision%20on%20a%20space%20policy%2C%20boost%20space-tech%2C%20propel%20its%20space%20economy%20and%20maximise%20its%20geopolitical%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20goals%20of%20becoming%20a%20permanent%20member%20of%20the%20U.N.%20Security%20Council%20is%20still%20unfulfilled%2C%20but%20it%20is%20now%20part%20of%20an%20elite%20group%20of%20nations%20that%20have%20been%20to%20the%20moon.%20These%20include%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20the%20United%20States.%20Several%20aspirants%2C%20including%20Israel%2C%20Japan%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20have%20not%20succeeded%20in%20landing%20on%20the%20moon's%20South%20Pole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENamrata%20Goswami%2C%20Professor%2C%20Space%20Policy%2C%20Thunderbird%20School%20of%20Global%20Management%2C%20Arizona%20State%20University%2C%20told%20NDTV%20that%20the%20success%20of%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%20sends%20a%20signal%20to%20the%20world%20that%20India%20has%20matured%20as%20a%20space%20power%2C%20and%20that%20it%20is%20no%20longer%20dependent%20on%20the%20perception%20that%20Russia%20was%20the%20so-called%20hand%20holder%20for%20India%20developing%20its%20space%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20stressing%20on%20the%20fact%20that%20space%20plays%20a%20critical%20part%20in%20augmenting%20the%20grand%20strategic%20notion%20of%20a%20nation%20as%20well%20as%20building%20its%20hard%20and%20soft%20power%2C%20and%20India%2C%20succeeding%20in%20its%20lunar%20mission%2C%20showcased%20the%20maturity%20and%20indigenous%20capacity%20of%20Indian%20space%20technology%2C%20Professor%20Goswami%2C%20however%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20where%20India%20is%20behind%20is%20in%20issuing%20a%20national%20security%20strategy%20and%20space%20policy%20where%20it%20clearly%20showcases%20how%20space%20is%20part%20of%20its%20grand%20strategic%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20such%20a%20strategy%20policy%2C%20technology%20demonstration%20may%20lack%20the%20strategic%20vision%20and%20focus%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20success%20of%20India's%20moon%20mission%20proves%20to%20the%20world%20that%20the%20country%20now%20has%20indigenous%20space%20capacity%20and%20has%20caught%20up%20with%20China%20on%20the%20Moon%2C%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20technologies%20like%20lunar%20landing%20and%20sending%20out%20a%20rover%20on%20a%20celestial%20body%20are%20concerned.%20%26quot%3BChina%20is%20ahead%20with%20its%20autonomous%20sample%20return%20where%20it%20returned%20lunar%20samples%20to%20Earth%20from%20the%20Moon%20in%202020%20and%20then%20the%20Chang'e%205%20went%20on%20to%20the%20Earth%20Sun%20Lagrange%20Point%201%2C%20an%20incredible%20demonstration%20of%20tech%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EG.%20Scott%20Hubbard%2C%20former%20NASA%20Ames%20Center%20Director%2C%20Department%20of%20Aeronautics%20and%20Astronautics%20Stanford%20University%2C%20said%20that%20significant%20achievements%20in%20space%20exploration%20are%20a%20major%20badge%20of%20accomplishment%20for%20any%20nation.%20%26quot%3BWith%20the%20success%20of%20MOM%20at%20Mars%20and%20now%20Chandrayaan%20at%20the%20Moon%2C%20India%20is%20showing%20noteworthy%20progress%20in%20space%20science%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStrategy%20for%20cislunar%20space%20needs%20planning%20and%20foresight%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Goswami%20explained%20that%20the%20space%20between%20the%20Earth%20and%20the%20Moon%20(cislunar)%20is%20a%20critical%20strategic%20area%20of%20great%20power%20competition%20with%20China's%20lunar%20mission%20focused%20on%20sending%20the%20Chang'e%206%20to%20the%20South%20Pole%20of%20the%20Moon%20next%20year%20to%20return%20samples.%20China%20and%20Russia%20are%20planning%20to%20establish%20a%20research%20base%20on%20the%20Moon%20by%202036%2C%20and%20that%20with%20India%20now%20successfully%20landing%20on%20the%20South%20Pole%2C%20such%20technology%20can%20be%20utilised%20for%20upcoming%20missions%20that%20are%20democratic%2C%20on%20the%20Moon%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20the%20success%20of%20Chandrayaan-3%20has%20major%20implications.%20%26quot%3BFor%20one%2C%20it%20showcases%20to%20countries%20like%20China%2C%20and%20now%20Russia%2C%20that%20India%20has%20moved%20ahead%20in%20cislunar%20(space%20between%20Earth%20and%20Moon)%20technology%20by%20showcasing%20autonomous%20lunar%20landing%2C%20sending%20out%20a%20rover%20and%20now%20searching%20the%20lunar%20regolith%20for%20elements%20like%20aluminium%2C%20magnesium%2C%20titanium%2C%20silicon%2C%20iron%20ore%20and%20water%20ice.%20Clinching%20a%20soft%20landing%20where%20all%20the%20sensors%2C%20radar%20system%2C%20propulsion%20system%20and%20braking%20system%20has%20to%20work%20is%20a%20major%20technological%20leap%20for%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGeopolitical%20gains%20for%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20success%20of%20India's%20moon%20mission%20will%20improve%20New%20Delhi's%20bargaining%20position%20vis-a-vis%20BRICS%20nation%2C%20which%20consists%20of%20China%20and%20Russia%20in%20collaborative%20efforts%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20Moon%2C%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20for%20the%20G-20%20summit%2C%20showcasing%20such%20advanced%20space%20technology%20builds%20reputation%20for%20innovation%2C%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20India%20did%20it%20indigenously%20adds%20to%20its%20persevering%20nature%20in%20regard%20to%20space%20technology%2C%20something%20other%20nations%20will%20notice%20and%20view%20India%20as%20a%20partner%20of%20choice%20in%20regard%20to%20space%20cooperation%2C%26quot%3B%20Professor%20Goswami%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20presence%20of%20water%2C%20which%20could%20be%20refined%20into%20rocket%20fuel%20in%20the%20future%2C%20suggests%20an%20opportunity%20for%20other%20countries%20to%20use%20the%20lunar%20South%20Pole%20region%20as%20a%20base%20for%20deeper%20space%20exploration%2C%20which%20is%20where%20experts%20feel%20India%20has%20an%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20way%20forward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20feel%20the%20lunar%20landing%20will%20also%20boost%20India's%20economy%20by%20kickstarting%20private%20space%20exploration%20programs.%20%26quot%3BEspecially%20after%20India%20has%20taken%20a%20major%20decision%20to%20orient%20its%20entire%20space%20ecosystem%20for%20privatisation.%20You%20see%2C%20this%20with%20its%202023%20space%20policy%20where%20the%20private%20sector%20will%20now%20be%20tasked%20and%20supported%20to%20manufacture%20the%20space%20systems%20that%20India%20will%20build%20going%20forward%2C%20with%20ISRO%20playing%20the%20key%20role%20of%20research%20and%20development.%20This%20will%20extend%20to%20the%20lunar%20missions%20as%20well%2C%20especially%20in%20building%20launch%20systems%20and%20lander%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20Professor%20Goswami%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20success%20of%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%20on%20Wednesday%20is%20likely%20to%20boost%20the%20Centre's%20ambitious%20Make-in-India%20programme%20by%20spurring%20investments%20in%20private%20space%20launches%20and%20related%20satellite-based%20businesses.%20Shares%20of%20Indian%20space-sector%20companies%20have%20rallied.%20The%20processors%20were%20built%20by%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology's%20SCL%20in%20Mohali%2C%20and%20they%20are%20expected%20to%20give%20a%20fillip%20to%20India's%20efforts%20to%20boost%20research%20in%20semiconductors%20too.%20In%20April%2C%20the%20government%20announced%20a%20landmark%20Space%20Policy%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20private%20sector%20access%20to%20a%20range%20of%20space%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Hubbard%20said%20that%20in%20the%20US%2C%20commercial%20Aviation%20is%20a%20larger%20market%20than%20space.%20However%2C%20the%20space%20market%20continues%20to%20grow%20every%20year.%20%26quot%3BThe%20success%20of%20SpaceX%2C%20Blue%20Origin%20and%20other%20smaller%20start-ups%20show%20there%20is%20clearly%20a%20low%20Earth%20Orbit%20space%20business%20developing.%20India%20might%20participate%20in%20this%20if%20it%20has%20three%20ingredients%3A%201)%20High%20net%20worth%20entrepreneurs%3B%202)%20Highly-trained%20aerospace%20engineers%3B%203)%20A%20business%20ecosystem%20that%20encourages%20such%20risk%20taking.%20It%20is%20no%20accident%20that%20SpaceX%20was%20founded%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20that%20Blue%20Origin%20is%20located%20in%20Seattle%3A%20home%20of%20Boeing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Goswami%20said%20India%20is%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%20Artemis%20Accords%20and%20the%20success%20of%20the%20Chandrayaan-3%20mission%20as%20well%20as%20the%20fact%20that%20its%20rover%20(Pragyan)%20is%20carrying%20an%20experiment%20to%20study%20the%20lunar%20elements%2C%20supports%20the%20Artemis%20Accords%20preamble%20that%20includes%20space%20resource%20utilisation%20and%20building%20sustainable%20lunar%20presence.%20%26quot%3BAs%20such%2C%20understanding%20the%20Moon's%20South%20Pole%20region%20is%20key.%20ISRO%20can%20play%20a%20role%20in%20research%20and%20development%20in%20partnership%20with%20NASA%20to%20further%20develop%20that%20end-to-end%20space%20capacity%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20new%20race%20in%20space%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20also%20feel%20the%20geopolitical%20rivalry%20among%20space%20faring%20nations%20could%20become%20stronger%20after%20Chandrayaan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20see%20the%20geopolitical%20angle%20of%20space%20with%20the%20U.S.%20drafted%20and%20now%20India%20signed%20Artemis%20Accords%20and%20the%20China-led%20and%20Russia%20signed%20International%20Lunar%20Research%20Station.%20There%20are%20several%20missions%20already%20planned%20for%20the%20Moon%20with%20a%202024%20China%20Lunar%20South%20Pole%20sample%20return%2C%202028%20South%20Pole%20survey%20mission%2C%202030%20Chinese%20taikonauts%20landing%20on%20the%20Moon%20and%20finally%20by%202036%20China%20building%20a%20research%20base%20in%20collaboration%20with%20Russia%2C%20Venezuela.%20Pakistan%20is%20also%20showing%20interest%20in%20joining%20China.%20This%20competition%20will%20play%20out%20based%20on%20who%20has%20a%20permanent%20presence%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%2C%20who%20will%20build%20that%20base%20first%2C%20as%20well%20as%20who%20will%20succeed%20in%20building%20the%20regulatory%20and%20normative%20regimes%20for%20the%20Moon%2C%26quot%3B%20Professor%20Goswami%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Hubbard%2C%20however%2C%20said%20people%20often%20speak%20of%20a%20Chinese-US%20space%20race%20to%20put%20humans%20on%20the%20Moon%20and%20Mars.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20Administrator%20of%20NASA%20has%20mentioned%20this%20in%20Congressional%20testimony%2C%20the%20overt%20attributes%20do%20not%20yet%20seem%20as%20evident%20as%20the%20US-Soviet%20%26quot%3Bspace%20race%26quot%3B%20of%20the%201960's%20Apollo%20era.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693380480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fo9pq521g_aditya-rocket-isro_625x300_30_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-now-needs-a-strategic-vision-for-space-boost-space-tech-experts-4341729%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Six%20decades%20after%20its%20first%20rocket%20launch%2C%20India%2C%20with%20the%20